1215
01:08:14,732 --> 01:08:17,132
The Game The Nation—Last Act

1216
01:08:17,132 --> 01:08:21,476
It has happened to you,
has it not, to wake in the morning and

1217
01:08:21,476 --> 01:08:24,597
wonder for a while where
on earth you are?

1218
01:08:24,597 --> 01:08:29,889
Thus I came half to life in the caboose,
hearing voices, but not the

1219
01:08:29,889 --> 01:08:32,229
actual words at first.

1220
01:08:32,229 --> 01:08:34,340
But presently, “Hathaway!”

1221
01:08:34,340 --> 01:08:35,943
said someone more clearly.

1222
01:08:35,943 --> 01:08:39,423
“Portland 1,291!”

1223
01:08:39,423 --> 01:08:43,862
This made no special stir in my
intelligence, and I drowsed off again to

1224
01:08:43,862 --> 01:08:46,937
the pleasant rhythm of the wheels.

1225
01:08:46,937 --> 01:08:50,816
The little shock of stopping next brought
me to, somewhat, with the voices still

1226
01:08:50,816 --> 01:08:54,220
round me; and when we were again in
motion, I heard: “Rosebud!

1227
01:08:54,220 --> 01:08:55,262
Portland

1228
01:08:55,262 --> -1:59:59,000
1,279

1229
-1:59:59,000 --> -1:59:59,000
!

1230
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

1231
01:08:56,639 --> 01:09:02,533
These figures jarred me awake,
and I said, “It was 1,291 before,”

1232
01:09:02,533 --> 01:09:04,393
and sat up in my blankets.

1233
01:09:04,393 --> 01:09:09,710
The greeting they vouchsafed and the
