1235
01:09:14,392 --> 01:09:19,245
Our next stop revealed how
things were going today.

1236
01:09:19,245 --> 01:09:21,920
“Forsythe,” one of them
read on the station.

1237
01:09:21,920 --> 01:09:24,988
“Portland 1,266.”

1238
01:09:24,988 --> 01:09:27,828
They were counting the
lessening distance westward.

1239
01:09:27,828 --> 01:09:31,823
This was the undercurrent of war.

1240
01:09:31,823 --> 01:09:38,222
It broke on me as I procured fresh water
at Forsythe and made some toilet

1241
01:09:38,222 --> 01:09:40,152
in their stolid presence.

1242
01:09:40,152 --> 01:09:44,759
We were drawing nearer the Rawhide
station⁠—the point, I mean,

1243
01:09:44,759 --> 01:09:48,139
where you left the railway
for the new mines.

1244
01:09:48,139 --> 01:09:51,638
Now Rawhide station lay
this side of Billings.

1245
01:09:51,638 --> 01:09:57,048
The broad path of desertion would open
