closer to his cooking.

1875
01:39:33,844 --> 01:39:36,260
“Oh, I don’t know,” said the traveller.

1876
01:39:36,260 --> 01:39:38,284
“We’ve paid pretty well, you see.”

1877
01:39:38,284 --> 01:39:42,768
“You’re late for Tulare,
Trampas,” said the Virginian.

1878
01:39:42,768 --> 01:39:46,720
“I was not thinking of
Tulare,” Trampas retorted.

1879
01:39:46,720 --> 01:39:50,553
Scipio’s nose was in the frying-pan.

1880
01:39:50,553 --> 01:39:53,022
“Mos’ comical spot you ever struck!”

1881
01:39:53,022 --> 01:39:56,558
said the Virginian, looking round
