But Lorenzo and Saynt Augustine was that
absorbed watchin’ each other⁠—for,

2098
01:51:20,434 --> 01:51:26,723
yu’ see, the Santa Fe and the Southern
Pacific come together at Mojave,

2099
01:51:26,723 --> 01:51:31,360
an’ the two cooks travelled a matter of
two hundred an’ ten miles in the same

2100
01:51:31,360 --> 01:51:34,763
cyar⁠—they never thought
about a telegram.

2101
01:51:34,763 --> 01:51:39,364
And when they arruv, breathless,
an’ started in to screechin’ what they’d

2102
01:51:39,364 --> 01:51:44,366
give for the monopoly,
why, them unsuspectin’ Tulare boys

2103
01:51:44,366 --> 01:51:45,872
got amused at ’em.

2104
01:51:45,872 --> 01:51:50,216
I never heard just all they done,
but they had Lorenzo singin’ and

2105
01:51:50,216 --> 01:51:54,709
dancin’, while Saynt Augustine played
the fiddle for him.

2106
01:51:54,709 --> 01:51:58,603
And one of Lorenzo’s heels did
get a trifle grazed.

2107
01:51:58,603 --> 01:52:04,283
Well, them two cooks quit that ranch
without disclosin’ their identity,

2108
01:52:04,283 --> 01:52:08,825
and soon as they got to a safe distance
they swore eternal friendship,

2109
01:52:08,825 --> 01:52:10,551
in their excitable foreign way.

2110
01:52:10,551 --> 01:52:14,519
And they went home over the Union
Pacific, sharing the same stateroom.

2111
01:52:14,519 --> 01:52:17,570
Their revenge killed frawgs.

2112
01:52:17,570 --> 01:52:18,768
The disease⁠—”

2113
01:52:18,768 --> 01:52:20,942
“How killed frogs?”

2114
01:52:20,942 --> 01:52:23,413
demanded Trampas.

2115
01:52:23,413 --> 01:52:25,013
“Just killed ’em.

2116
01:52:25,013 --> 01:52:30,289
Delmonico and Saynt Augustine wiped
frawgs off the slate of fashion.

2117
01:52:30,289 --> 01:52:34,045
Not a banker in Fifth Avenue’ll touch one
now if another banker’s

2118
01:52:34,045 --> 01:52:35,125
around watchin’ him.

2119
01:52:35,125 --> 01:52:39,985
And if ever yu’ see a man that hides his
feet an’ won’t take off his socks in

2120
01:52:39,985 --> 01:52:44,378
company, he has worked in them Tulare
swamps an’ got the disease.

2121
01:52:44,378 --> 01:52:47,427
Catch him wadin’, and yu’ll
find he’s web-footed.

2122
01:52:47,427 --> -1:59:59,000
Frawgs are dead, Trampas, and so are you.

2123
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2124
01:52:50,890 --> 01:52:54,480
“Rise up, liars, and salute your king!”

2125
01:52:54,480 --> 01:52:55,758
yelled Scipio.

2126
01:52:55,758 --> 01:52:57,985
“Oh, I’m in love with you!”

2127
01:52:57,985 --> 01:53:00,288
And he threw his arms round the Virginian.

2128
01:53:00,288 --> 01:53:05,172
“Let me shake hands with you,”
said the traveller, who had failed to

2129
01:53:05,172 --> 01:53:07,410
interest his wife in these things.

2130
01:53:07,410 --> 01:53:09,834
“I wish I was going to have
more of your company.”

2131
01:53:09,834 --> 01:53:12,647
“Thank yu’, seh,” said the Virginian.

2132
01:53:12,647 --> 01:53:15,570
Other passengers greeted him,
and the Indian chiefs

2133
01:53:15,570 --> 01:53:17,517
came, saying, “How!”

2134
01:53:17,517 --> 01:53:19,993
because they followed
their feelings without understanding.

2135
01:53:19,993 --> 01:53:23,810
“Don’t show so humbled,
boys,” said the deputy foreman to

2136
01:53:23,810 --> 01:53:25,295
his most sheepish crew.

2137
01:53:25,295 --> 01:53:30,156
“These gentlemen from the East have been
enjoying yu’ some, I know.

2138
01:53:30,156 --> 01:53:33,334
But think what a weary wait
they have had hyeh.

2139
01:53:33,334 --> 01:53:39,041
And you insisted on playing the game with
me this way, yu’ see.

2140
01:53:39,041 --> 01:53:41,513
What outlet did yu’ give me?

2141
01:53:41,513 --> 01:53:43,078
Didn’t I have it to do?

2142
01:53:43,078 --> 01:53:46,475
And I’ll tell yu’ one thing for your
consolation: when I got to the middle of

2143
01:53:46,475 --> 01:53:48,905
the frawgs I ’most believed it myself.”

2144
01:53:48,905 --> 01:53:52,540
And he laughed out the first laugh I
had heard him give.

2145
01:53:52,540 --> 01:53:55,142
The enthusiast came up and shook hands.

2146
01:53:55,142 --> 01:54:00,042
That led off, and the rest followed,
with Trampas at the end.

2147
01:54:00,042 --> 01:54:02,971
The tide was too strong for him.

2148
01:54:02,971 --> 01:54:05,802
He was not a graceful loser;
but he got through this,

2149
01:54:05,802 --> 01:54:09,282
and the Virginian eased him down by
treating him precisely

2150
01:54:09,282 --> 01:54:11,743
like the others⁠—apparently.

2151
01:54:11,743 --> 01:54:16,456
Possibly the supreme⁠—the most American⁠—
moment of all was when word came that the

2152
01:54:16,456 --> 01:54:20,692
bridge was open, and the Pullman trains,
with noise and triumph,

2153
01:54:20,692 --> 01:54:22,928
began to move westward at last.

2154
01:54:22,928 --> 01:54:29,298
Everyone waved farewell to everyone,
craning from steps and windows,

2155
01:54:29,298 --> 01:54:33,050
so that the cars twinkled with hilarity;
and in twenty minutes the whole

2156
01:54:33,050 --> 01:54:36,106
procession in front had moved,
and our turn came.

2157
01:54:36,106 --> 01:54:39,092
“Last chance for Rawhide,”
said the Virginian.

2158
01:54:39,092 --> 01:54:43,750
“Last chance for Sunk Creek,”
said a reconstructed mutineer,

2159
01:54:43,750 --> 01:54:45,353
and all sprang aboard.

2160
01:54:45,353 --> 01:54:48,957
There was no question who had
won his spurs now.

2161
01:54:48,957 --> 01:54:54,821
Our caboose trundled on to Billings along
the shingly cotton-wooded Yellowstone;

2162
01:54:54,821 --> 01:55:00,154
and as the plains and bluffs and the
distant snow began to grow well known,

2163
01:55:00,154 --> 01:55:04,086
even to me, we turned to our baggage
that was to come off,

2164
01:55:04,086 --> 01:55:09,592
since camp would begin in the morning.

2165
01:55:12,525 --> 01:55:16,327
Thus I saw the Virginian carefully
rewrapping Kenilworth,

2166
01:55:16,327 --> 01:55:20,173
that he might bring it to its owner
unharmed; and I said,

2167
01:55:20,173 --> 01:55:23,582
“Don’t you think you could have played
poker with Queen Elizabeth?”

2168
01:55:23,582 --> 01:55:28,537
“No; I expaict she’d have
beat me,” he replied.

2169
01:55:28,537 --> 01:55:29,729
“She was a lady.”

2170
01:55:29,729 --> 01:55:33,808
It was at Billings, on this day,
that I made those reflections

2171
01:55:33,808 --> 01:55:34,982
about equality.

2172
01:55:34,982 --> 01:55:39,049
For the Virginian had been equal to the
occasion: that is the only kind of

2173
01:55:39,049 --> 01:55:41,748
equality which I recognize.

2174
01:55:41,748 --> 01:55:42,961
CHAPTER XVII

2175
01:55:42,961 --> 01:55:44,420
Scipio Moralizes

2176
01:55:44,420 --> 01:55:48,156
Into what mood was it that
the Virginian now fell?

2177
01:55:48,156 --> 01:55:52,736
Being less busy, did he begin to “grieve”
about the girl on Bear Creek?

2178
01:55:52,736 --> 01:55:56,438
I only know that after talking so
lengthily he fell into

2179
01:55:56,438 --> 01:55:58,087
a nine days’ silence.

2180
01:55:58,087 --> 01:56:02,824
The talking part of him
deeply and unbrokenly slept.

2181
01:56:02,824 --> 01:56:07,112
Official words of course came from him as
we rode southward from the railroad,

2182
01:56:07,112 --> 01:56:09,453
gathering the Judge’s stray cattle.

2183
01:56:09,453 --> 01:56:14,094
During the many weeks since the spring
roundup, some of these animals had as

2184
01:56:14,094 --> 01:56:23,347
usual got very far off their range,
and getting them on again became the

2185
01:56:23,347 --> 01:56:26,267
present business of our party.

2186
01:56:26,267 --> 01:56:31,252
Directions and commands⁠—whatever
communications to his subordinates were

2187
01:56:31,252 --> 01:56:34,944
needful to the forwarding of
this⁠—he duly gave.

2188
01:56:34,944 --> 01:56:41,632
But routine has never at any time of the
world passed for conversation.

2189
01:56:41,632 --> 01:56:46,244
His utterances, such as,
“We’ll work Willo’ Creek tomorro’

2190
01:56:46,244 --> 01:56:50,523
mawnin’,” or, “I want the wagon to be at
the fawks o’ Stinkin’ Water by

2191
01:56:50,523 --> 01:56:55,736
Thursday,” though on some occasions
numerous enough to sound like discourse,

2192
01:56:55,736 --> 01:56:58,611
never once broke the man’s true silence.

2193
01:56:58,611 --> 01:57:04,350
Seeming to keep easy company with the
camp, he yet kept altogether to himself.

2194
01:57:04,350 --> 01:57:09,510
That talking part of him⁠—the mood which
brings out for you your friend’s spirit

2195
01:57:09,510 --> 01:57:16,370
and mind as a free gift or as an
exchange⁠—was down in some dark cave of

2196
01:57:16,370 --> 01:57:18,608
his nature, hidden away.

2197
01:57:18,608 --> 01:57:22,749
Perhaps it had been dreaming;
perhaps completely reposing.

2198
01:57:22,749 --> 01:57:26,573
The Virginian was one of those rare ones
who are able to refresh

2199
01:57:26,573 --> 01:57:29,487
themselves in sections.

2200
01:57:29,487 --> 01:57:33,991
To have a thing on his mind did not keep
his body from resting.

2201
01:57:33,991 --> 01:57:38,391
During our recent journey⁠—it felt years
ago now!⁠—while our caboose on the

2202
01:57:38,391 --> 01:57:42,591
freight train had trundled endlessly
westward, and the men were on the ragged

2203
01:57:42,591 --> 01:57:48,029
edge, the very jumping-off place,
of mutiny and possible murder,

2204
01:57:48,029 --> 01:57:53,390
I had seen him sleep like a child.

2205
01:57:53,390 --> 01:57:56,745
He snatched the moments
not necessary for vigil.

2206
01:57:56,745 --> 01:58:00,964
I had also seen him sit all night
watching his responsibility,

2207
01:58:00,964 --> 01:58:03,574
ready to spring on it and fasten
his teeth in it.

2208
01:58:03,574 --> 01:58:10,204
And now that he had confounded them with
their own attempted weapon of ridicule,

2209
01:58:10,204 --> 01:58:13,212
his powers seemed to
be profoundly dormant.

2210
01:58:13,212 --> 01:58:17,551
That final pitched battle of wits had
made the men his captives and

2211
01:58:17,551 --> 01:58:20,723
admirers⁠—all save Trampas.

2212
01:58:20,723 --> 01:58:24,169
And of him the Virginian did not
seem to be aware.

2213
01:58:24,169 --> 01:58:27,844
But Scipio le Moyne would say to me now
and then, “If I was Trampas,

2214
01:58:27,844 --> 01:58:29,295
I’d pull my freight.”

2215
01:58:29,295 --> 01:58:32,365
And once he added, “Pull it kind of
casual, yu’ know, like I wasn’t

2216
01:58:32,365 --> -1:59:59,000
noticing myself do it.

2217
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2218
01:58:33,956 --> 01:58:40,089
“Yes,” our friend Shorty murmured
pregnantly, with his eye upon the quiet

2219
01:58:40,089 --> 01:58:44,067
Virginian, “he’s sure
studying his revenge.”

2220
01:58:44,067 --> 01:58:46,895
“Studying your pussycat,” said Scipio.

2221
01:58:46,895 --> 01:58:49,015
“He knows what he’ll do.

2222
01:58:49,015 --> 01:58:50,436
The time ain’t arrived.”

2223
01:58:50,436 --> 01:58:53,835
This was the way they felt about it;
and not unnaturally this was the way

2224
01:58:53,835 --> 01:58:57,174
they made me, the inexperienced
Easterner, feel about it.

2225
01:58:57,174 --> 01:59:02,433
That Trampas also felt something about it
was easy to know.

2226
01:59:02,433 --> 01:59:08,276
Like the leaven which leavens the whole
lump, one spot of sulkiness in camp will

2227
01:59:08,276 --> 01:59:12,049
spread its dull flavor through any
company that sits near it;

2228
01:59:12,049 --> 01:59:16,439
and we had to sit near Trampas at
meals for nine days.

2229
01:59:16,439 --> 01:59:18,132
His sullenness was not wonderful.

2230
01:59:18,132 --> 01:59:23,259
To feel himself forsaken by his recent
adherents, to see them gone over to his

2231
01:59:23,259 --> 01:59:26,828
enemy, could not have
made his reflections pleasant.

2232
01:59:26,828 --> 01:59:32,240
Why he did not take himself off to other
climes⁠—“pull his freight casual,”

2233
01:59:32,240 --> 01:59:37,955
as Scipio said⁠—I can explain only thus:
pay was due him⁠—“time,”

2234
01:59:37,955 --> 01:59:42,590
as it was called in cow-land;
if he would have this money,

2235
01:59:42,590 --> 01:59:47,131
he must stay under the Virginian’s
command until the Judge’s ranch on Sunk

2236
01:59:47,131 --> 01:59:51,824
Creek should be reached;
meanwhile, each day’s work added to the

2237
01:59:51,824 --> 01:59:56,491
wages in store for him;
and finally, once at Sunk Creek,

2238
01:59:56,491 --> 01:59:59,885
it would be no more the Virginian who
commanded him; it would be

2239
01:59:59,885 --> 02:00:01,445
the real ranch foreman.

2240
02:00:01,445 --> 02:00:05,405
At the ranch he would be the Virginian’s
equal again, both of them taking orders

2241
02:00:05,405 --> 02:00:09,014
from their officially
recognized superior, this foreman.

2242
02:00:09,014 --> 02:00:14,863
Shorty’s word about “revenge” seemed to
me like putting the thing backwards.

2243
02:00:14,863 --> 02:00:20,508
Revenge, as I told Scipio,
was what I should be thinking about

2244
02:00:20,508 --> 02:00:22,236
if I were Trampas.

2245
02:00:22,236 --> 02:00:26,680
“He dassent,” was Scipio’s immediate view.

2246
02:00:26,680 --> 02:00:29,458
“Not till he’s got strong again.

2247
02:00:29,458 --> 02:00:33,961
He got laughed plumb sick by the
bystanders, and whatever spirit he had

2248
02:00:33,961 --> 02:00:36,159
was broke in the presence of us all.

2249
02:00:36,159 --> 02:00:37,431
He’ll have to recuperate.”

2250
02:00:37,431 --> 02:00:40,111
Scipio then spoke of the
Virginian’s attitude.

2251
02:00:40,111 --> 02:00:44,071
“Maybe revenge ain’t just the right word
for where this affair has got

2252
02:00:44,071 --> 02:00:45,079
to now with him.

2253
02:00:45,079 --> 02:00:49,270
When yu’ beat another man at his own game
like he done to Trampas,

2254
02:00:49,270 --> 02:00:53,115
why, yu’ve had all the revenge yu’ can
want, unless you’re a hog.

2255
02:00:53,115 --> 02:00:54,349
And he’s no hog.

2256
02:00:54,349 --> 02:00:56,337
But he has got it in for Trampas.

2257
02:00:56,337 --> 02:00:58,385
They’ve not reckoned to a finish.

2258
02:00:58,385 --> 02:01:02,438
Would you let a man try such spite-work
on you and quit thinkin’ about him just

2259
02:01:02,438 --> 02:01:03,870
because yu’d headed him off?”

2260
02:01:03,870 --> 02:01:07,747
To this I offered his own notion about
hogs and being satisfied.

2261
02:01:07,747 --> 02:01:09,249
“Hogs!”

2262
02:01:09,249 --> 02:01:13,529
went on Scipio, in a way that dashed my
suggestion to pieces;

2263
02:01:13,529 --> 02:01:16,729
“hogs ain’t in the case.

2264
02:01:16,729 --> 02:01:21,601
He’s got to deal with Trampas
somehow⁠—man to man.

2265
02:01:21,601 --> 02:01:32,228
Trampas and him can’t stay this way when
they get back and go workin’ same

2266
02:01:32,228 --> 02:01:35,428
as they worked before.

2267
02:01:35,428 --> 02:01:40,331
No, sir; I’ve seen his eye twice,
and I know he’s goin’ to

2268
02:01:40,331 --> -1:59:59,000
reckon to a finish.

2269
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2270
02:01:41,571 --> 02:01:46,346
I still must, in Scipio’s opinion,
have been slow to understand,

2271
02:01:46,346 --> 02:01:50,513
when on the afternoon following this
talk I invited him to tell me what sort

2272
02:01:50,513 --> 02:01:55,257
of “finish” he wanted,
after such a finishing as had

2273
02:01:55,257 --> 02:01:58,038
been dealt Trampas already.

2274
02:01:58,038 --> 02:02:02,810
Getting “laughed plumb sick by the
bystanders” (I borrowed his own not

2275
02:02:02,810 --> 02:02:08,145
overstated expression) seemed to me
a highly final finishing.

2276
02:02:08,145 --> 02:02:12,638
While I was running my notions off to
him, Scipio rose, and,

2277
02:02:12,638 --> 02:02:16,917
with the frying-pan he had been washing,
walked slowly at me.

2278
02:02:16,917 --> 02:02:21,210
“I do believe you’d oughtn’t to be let
travel alone the way you do.”

2279
02:02:21,210 --> 02:02:23,169
He put his face close to mine.

2280
02:02:23,169 --> 02:02:28,579
His long nose grew eloquent in its
shrewdness, while the fire in his

2281
02:02:28,579 --> 02:02:31,533
bleached blue eye burned
with amiable satire.

2282
02:02:31,533 --> 02:02:35,853
“What has come and gone between them two
has only settled the one point he

2283
02:02:35,853 --> 02:02:37,238
was aimin’ to make.

2284
02:02:37,238 --> 02:02:41,279
He was appointed boss of this outfit in
the absence of the regular foreman.

2285
02:02:41,279 --> 02:02:45,893
Since then all he has been playin’ for is
to hand back his men to the ranch in as

2286
02:02:45,893 --> 02:02:49,774
good shape as they’d been handed to him,
and without losing any on the road

2287
02:02:49,774 --> 02:02:52,884
through desertion or shooting or
whatnot.

2288
02:02:52,884 --> 02:02:56,604
He had to kick his cook off the train
that day, and the loss made him

2289
02:02:56,604 --> 02:02:58,335
sorrowful, I could see.

2290
02:02:58,335 --> 02:03:02,249
But I’d happened to come along,
and he jumped me into the vacancy,

2291
02:03:02,249 --> 02:03:04,683
and I expect he is pretty near consoled.

2292
02:03:04,683 --> 02:03:08,854
And as boss of the outfit he beat
Trampas, who was settin’

2293
02:03:08,854 --> 02:03:10,534
up for opposition boss.

2294
02:03:10,534 --> 02:03:14,214
And the outfit is better than satisfied
it come out that way,

2295
02:03:14,214 --> 02:03:17,414
and they’re stayin’ with him;
and he’ll hand them all back in good

2296
02:03:17,414 --> 02:03:21,149
condition, barrin’ that lost cook.

2297
02:03:21,149 --> 02:03:24,249
So for the present his point
is made, yu’ see.

2298
02:03:24,249 --> 02:03:25,655
But look ahead a little.

2299
02:03:25,655 --> 02:03:29,083
It may not be so very far ahead
yu’ll have to look.

2300
02:03:29,083 --> 02:03:30,869
We get back to the ranch.

2301
02:03:30,869 --> 02:03:32,959
He’s not boss there any more.

2302
02:03:32,959 --> 02:03:35,478
His responsibility is over.

2303
02:03:35,478 --> 02:03:39,299
He is just one of us again,
taking orders from a foreman they tell

2304
02:03:39,299 --> 02:03:43,198
me has showed partiality to Trampas
more’n a few times.

2305
02:03:43,198 --> 02:03:44,503
Partiality!

2306
02:03:44,503 --> 02:03:47,923
That’s what Trampas is
plainly trusting to.

2307
02:03:47,923 --> 02:03:52,332
Trusting it will fix him all right and
fix his enemy all wrong.

2308
02:03:52,332 --> 02:03:56,716
He’d not otherwise dare to keep
sour like he’s doing.

2309
02:03:56,716 --> 02:03:58,114
Partiality!

2310
02:03:58,114 --> 02:04:00,125
D’ yu’ think it’ll scare off the enemy?”

2311
02:04:00,125 --> 02:04:04,065
Scipio looked across a little creek to
where the Virginian was helping throw

2312
02:04:04,065 --> 02:04:06,565
the gathered cattle on the bedground.

2313
02:04:06,565 --> 02:04:14,892
“What odds”⁠—he pointed the frying-pan at
the Southerner⁠—“d’ yu’ figure Trampas’s

2314
02:04:14,892 --> 02:04:19,092
being under any foreman’s wing will make
to a man like him?

2315
02:04:19,092 --> 02:04:23,208
He’s going to remember Mr. Trampas and
his spite-work if he’s got to tear him

2316
02:04:23,208 --> 02:04:25,568
out from under the wing,
and maybe tear off the

2317
02:04:25,568 --> 02:04:26,876
wing in the operation.

2318
02:04:26,876 --> 02:04:30,798
And I am goin’ to advise your folks,”
ended the complete Scipio,

2319
02:04:30,798 --> -1:59:59,000
“not to leave you travel so much alone⁠—
not till you’ve learned more life

2320
-1:59:59,000 --> -1:59:59,000
.

2321
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2322
02:04:35,828 --> 02:04:41,077
He had made me feel my inexperience,
convinced me of innocence,

2323
02:04:41,077 --> 02:04:46,652
undoubtedly; and during the final days
of our journey I no longer invoked his

2324
02:04:46,652 --> 02:04:52,508
aid to my reflections upon this especial
topic: What would the

2325
02:04:52,508 --> 02:04:55,444
Virginian do to Trampas?

2326
02:04:55,444 --> 02:04:59,838
Would it be another intellectual crushing
of him, like the frog story,

2327
02:04:59,838 --> 02:05:03,828
or would there be something this time
more material⁠—say muscle,

2328
02:05:03,828 --> 02:05:06,005
or possibly gunpowder⁠—in it?

2329
02:05:06,005 --> 02:05:09,725
And was Scipio, after all, infallible?

2330
02:05:09,725 --> 02:05:14,239
I didn’t pretend to understand the
Virginian; after several years’

2331
02:05:14,239 --> 02:05:18,442
knowledge of him he remained
utterly beyond me.

2332
02:05:18,442 --> 02:05:23,168
Scipio’s experience was not
yet three weeks long.

2333
02:05:23,168 --> 02:05:27,982
So I let him alone as to all this,
discussing with him most other things

2334
02:05:27,982 --> 02:05:31,022
good and evil in the world,
and being convinced of much further

2335
02:05:31,022 --> 02:05:38,651
innocence; for Scipio’s twenty odd years
were indeed a library of life.

2336
02:05:38,651 --> 02:05:44,495
I have never met a better heart,
a shrewder wit, and looser morals,

2337
02:05:44,495 --> 02:05:50,767
with yet a native sense of decency and
duty somewhere hard and fast enshrined.

2338
02:05:50,767 --> 02:05:54,912
But all the while I was wondering about
the Virginian: eating with him,

2339
02:05:54,912 --> 02:05:58,911
sleeping with him (only not so sound as
he did), and riding beside him

2340
02:05:58,911 --> 02:06:00,743
often for many hours.

2341
02:06:00,743 --> 02:06:04,351
Experiments in conversation I
did make⁠—and failed.

2342
02:06:04,351 --> 02:06:09,174
One day particularly while,
after a sudden storm of hail had chilled

2343
02:06:09,174 --> 02:06:14,796
the earth numb and white like winter in
fifteen minutes, we sat drying and

2344
02:06:14,796 --> 02:06:19,747
warming ourselves by a fire that we
built, I touched upon that theme of

2345
02:06:19,747 --> 02:06:25,458
equality on which I knew him to hold
opinions as strong as mine.

2346
02:06:25,458 --> 02:06:30,845
“Oh,” he would reply,
and “Cert’nly”; and when I asked him

2347
02:06:30,845 --> 02:06:34,995
what it was in a man that made him a
leader of men, he shook his head

2348
02:06:34,995 --> 02:06:36,075
and puffed his pipe.

2349
02:06:36,075 --> 02:06:41,409
So then, noticing how the sun had brought
the earth in half an hour back from

2350
02:06:41,409 --> 02:06:44,809
winter to summer again,
I spoke of our American climate.

2351
02:06:44,809 --> 02:06:47,689
It was a potent drug,
I said, for millions to

2352
02:06:47,689 --> 02:06:49,169
be swallowing every day.

2353
02:06:49,169 --> 02:06:54,797
“Yes,” said he, wiping the damp
from his Winchester rifle.

2354
02:06:54,797 --> 02:06:59,293
Our American climate,
I said, had worked remarkable

2355
02:06:59,293 --> 02:07:01,174
changes, at least.

2356
02:07:01,174 --> 02:07:04,379
“Yes,” he said; and did not
ask what they were.

2357
02:07:04,379 --> 02:07:06,164
So I had to tell him.

2358
02:07:06,164 --> 02:07:11,293
“It has made successful
politicians of the Irish.

2359
02:07:11,293 --> 02:07:12,669
That’s one.

2360
02:07:12,669 --> 02:07:17,595
And it has given our whole race
the habit of poker.”

2361
02:07:17,595 --> 02:07:19,488
Bang went his Winchester.

2362
02:07:19,488 --> 02:07:21,878
The bullet struck close to my left.

2363
02:07:21,878 --> 02:07:24,298
I sat up angrily.

2364
02:07:24,298 --> 02:07:26,963
“That’s the first foolish thing I
ever saw you do!”

2365
02:07:26,963 --> 02:07:28,099
I said.

2366
02:07:28,099 --> 02:07:31,789
“Yes,” he drawled slowly,
“I’d ought to have done it sooner.

2367
02:07:31,789 --> 02:07:33,608
He was pretty near lively again.”

2368
02:07:33,608 --> 02:07:38,185
And then he picked up a rattlesnake
six feet behind me.

2369
02:07:38,185 --> 02:07:41,915
It had been numbed by the hail,
part revived by the sun,

2370
02:07:41,915 --> 02:07:43,801
and he had shot its head off.

2371
02:07:43,801 --> 02:07:44,980
CHAPTER XVIII

2372
02:07:44,980 --> 02:07:46,106
“Would You Be a Parson?”

2373
02:07:46,106 --> 02:07:48,805
After this I gave up my
experiments in conversation.

2374
02:07:48,805 --> 02:07:54,806
So that by the final afternoon of our
journey, with Sunk Creek actually in

2375
02:07:54,806 --> 02:07:59,006
sight, and the great grasshoppers
slatting their dry song over the

2376
02:07:59,006 --> 02:08:04,286
sagebrush, and the time at hand when the
Virginian and Trampas would be “man to

2377
02:08:04,286 --> 02:08:09,535
man,” my thoughts rose to a
considerable pitch of speculation.

2378
02:08:09,535 --> 02:08:13,348
And now that talking part of the
Virginian, which had been nine days

2379
02:08:13,348 --> 02:08:17,155
asleep, gave its first yawn
and stretch of waking.

2380
02:08:17,155 --> 02:08:20,710
Without preface, he suddenly asked me,
“Would you be a parson?”

2381
02:08:20,710 --> 02:08:25,830
I was mentally so far away that I
couldn’t get back in time to comprehend

2382
02:08:25,830 --> 02:08:29,470
or answer before he had repeated:⁠—

2383
02:08:29,470 --> 02:08:33,334
“What would yu’ take to be a parson?”

2384
02:08:33,334 --> 02:08:37,894
He drawled it out in his gentle way,
precisely as if no nine days stood

2385
02:08:37,894 --> 02:08:42,086
between it and our last real
intercourse.

2386
02:08:42,086 --> 02:08:42,626
“Take?”

2387
02:08:42,626 --> 02:08:46,637
I was still vaguely moving in my distance.

2388
02:08:46,637 --> 02:08:47,366
“How?”

2389
02:08:47,366 --> 02:08:49,531
His next question brought me home.

2390
02:08:49,531 --> 02:08:53,141
“I expect the Pope’s is the biggest
of them parson jobs?”

2391
02:08:53,141 --> 02:08:55,299
It was with an “Oh!”

2392
02:08:55,299 --> 02:08:57,409
that I now entirely took his idea.

2393
02:08:57,409 --> 02:09:00,601
“Well, yes; decidedly the biggest.”

2394
02:09:00,601 --> 02:09:02,264
“Beats the English one?

2395
02:09:02,264 --> 02:09:05,124
Archbishop⁠—ain’t it?⁠—of Canterbury?

2396
02:09:05,124 --> 02:09:06,707
The Pope comes ahead of him?”

2397
02:09:06,707 --> 02:09:09,724
“His Holiness would say so if
his Grace did not.”

2398
02:09:09,724 --> 02:09:13,404
The Virginian turned half in his saddle
to see my face⁠—I was,

2399
02:09:13,404 --> 02:09:17,796
at the moment, riding not quite abreast
of him⁠—and I saw the gleam of his

2400
02:09:17,796 --> 02:09:20,229
teeth beneath his mustache.

2401
02:09:20,229 --> 02:09:25,333
It was seldom I could make him smile,
even to this slight extent.

2402
02:09:25,333 --> 02:09:31,067
But his eyes grew, with his next words,
remote again in their speculation.

2403
02:09:31,067 --> 02:09:34,115
“His Holiness and his Grace.

2404
02:09:34,115 --> 02:09:39,583
Now if I was to hear ’em namin’ me that-
a-way every mawnin’, I’d sca’cely

2405
02:09:39,583 --> -1:59:59,000
get down to business.

2406
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2407
02:09:40,884 --> 02:09:42,462
“Oh, you’d get used to the pride of it.”

2408
02:09:42,462 --> 02:09:43,484
“ ’Tisn’t the pride.

2409
02:09:43,484 --> 02:09:45,011
The laugh is what would ruin me.

2410
02:09:45,011 --> 02:09:48,604
’Twould take ’most all my attention
keeping a straight face.

2411
02:09:48,604 --> 02:09:54,347
The Archbishop”⁠—here he took one of his
wide mental turns⁠—“is apt to be a big

2412
02:09:54,347 --> 02:09:56,428
man in them Shakespeare plays.

2413
02:09:56,428 --> 02:10:00,739
Kings take talk from him they’d not stand
from anybody else; and

2414
02:10:00,739 --> 02:10:03,021
he talks fine, frequently.

2415
02:10:03,021 --> 02:10:08,122
About the bees, for instance,
when Henry is going to fight France.

2416
02:10:08,122 --> 02:10:12,570
He tells him a beehive is
similar to a kingdom.

2417
02:10:12,570 --> 02:10:14,200
I learned that piece.”

2418
02:10:14,200 --> 02:10:19,133
The Virginian could not have expected to
blush at uttering these last words.

2419
02:10:19,133 --> 02:10:23,352
He knew that his sudden color must tell
me in whose book it was he

2420
02:10:23,352 --> 02:10:24,977
had learned the piece.

2421
02:10:24,977 --> 02:10:29,297
Was not her copy of Kenilworth even now
in his cherishing pocket?

2422
02:10:29,297 --> 02:10:35,276
So he now, to cover his blush,
very deliberately recited to me the

2423
02:10:35,276 --> 02:10:40,156
Archbishop’s discourse upon
bees and their kingdom:⁠—

2424
02:10:40,156 --> 02:10:45,254
“ ‘Where some, like magistrates,
correct at home.

2425
02:10:45,254 --> 02:10:47,106
⋮Others, like soldiers,
armèd in their stings,

2426
02:10:47,106 --> 02:10:50,921
