2439
02:11:28,594 --> 02:11:30,315
“Two kinds!”

2440
02:11:30,315 --> 02:11:31,015
I put in.

2441
02:11:31,015 --> 02:11:33,453
“At least two of Episcopals.”

2442
02:11:33,453 --> 02:11:34,498
“That’s three.

2443
02:11:34,498 --> 02:11:38,637
Then Methodists and Baptists, and⁠—”

2444
02:11:38,637 --> 02:11:41,545
“Three Methodists!”

2445
02:11:41,545 --> 02:11:43,929
“Well, you do the countin’.”

2446
02:11:43,929 --> 02:11:49,255
I accordingly did it,
feeling my revolving memory slip cogs

2447
02:11:49,255 --> 02:11:50,906
all the way round.

2448
02:11:50,906 --> 02:11:53,624
“Anyhow, there are safely fifteen.”

2449
02:11:53,624 --> 02:11:54,379
“Fifteen.”

2450
02:11:54,379 --> 02:11:56,339
He held this fact a moment.

2451
02:11:56,339 --> 02:12:01,221
“And they don’t worship a whole heap o’
different gods like the ancients did?”

2452
02:12:01,221 --> 02:12:05,461
“Oh, no!”

2453
02:12:05,461 --> 02:12:07,342
“It’s just the same one?”

2454
02:12:07,342 --> 02:12:08,341
“The same one.”

2455
02:12:08,341 --> 02:12:13,642
The Virginian folded his hands over the
horn of his saddle, and leaned forward

2456
02:12:13,642 --> 02:12:19,287
upon them in contemplation of
the wide, beautiful landscape.

2457
02:12:19,287 --> 02:12:21,850
“One God and fifteen religions

2458
02:12:21,850 --> 02:12:23,207
,” was his reflection.

2459
02:12:23,207 --> 02:12:26,761
“That’s a right smart of religions
for just one God.”

2460
02:12:26,761 --> 02:12:32,366
This way of reducing it was,
if obvious to him, so novel to me that

2461
02:12:32,366 --> 02:12:38,269
my laugh evidently struck him as a
louder and livelier comment

2462
02:12:38,269 --> 02:12:40,291
than was required.

2463
02:12:40,291 --> 02:12:45,611
He turned on me as if I had somehow
perverted the spirit of his words.

2464
02:12:45,611 --> 02:12:46,933
“I ain’t religious.

2465
02:12:46,933 --> 02:12:47,804
I know that.

2466
02:12:47,804 --> 02:12:49,586
But I ain’t unreligious.

2467
02:12:49,586 --> 02:12:50,779
And I know that too.”

2468
02:12:50,779 --> 02:12:52,386
“So do I know it, my friend.”

2469
02:12:52,386 --> 02:12:55,865
“Do you think there ought to be fifteen
varieties of good people?”

2470
02:12:55,865 --> 02:13:00,306
His voice, while it now had an edge that
could cut anything it came against,

2471
02:13:00,306 --> 02:13:02,946
was still not raised.

2472
02:13:02,946 --> 02:13:05,337
“There ain’t fifteen.

2473
02:13:05,337 --> 02:13:06,603
There ain’t two.

2474
02:13:06,603 --> 02:13:08,191
There’s one kind.

2475
02:13:08,191 --> 02:13:10,322
And when I meet it, I respect it.

2476
02:13:10,322 --> 02:13:14,900
It is not praying nor preaching that has
ever caught me and made me ashamed of

2477
02:13:14,900 --> 02:13:18,253
myself, but one or two people I have
knowed that never said a

2478
02:13:18,253 --> 02:13:19,693
superior word to me.

2479
02:13:19,693 --> 02:13:23,693
They thought more o’ me than I deserved,
and that made me behave better than

2480
02:13:23,693 --> 02:13:25,156
I naturally wanted to.

2481
02:13:25,156 --> 02:13:29,533
Made me quit a girl onced in time for her
not to lose her good name.

2482
02:13:29,533 --> 02:13:32,783
And so that’s one thing I have never done.

2483
02:13:32,783 --> 02:13:38,090
And if ever I was to have a son or
somebody I set store by,

2484
02:13:38,090 --> 02:13:44,023
I would wish their lot to be to know one
or two good folks mighty well⁠—men

2485
02:13:44,023 --> -1:59:59,000
or women⁠—women preferred.

2486
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2487
02:13:47,079 --> 02:13:51,713
He had looked away again to the hills
behind Sunk Creek ranch,

2488
02:13:51,713 --> 02:13:55,366
to which our walking horses had
now almost brought us.

2489
02:13:55,366 --> 02:13:59,997
“As for parsons”⁠—the gesture of his arm
was a disclaiming one⁠—“I reckon some

2490
02:13:59,997 --> 02:14:02,708
parsons have a right to tell
yu’ to be good.

2491
02:14:02,708 --> 02:14:06,860
The bishop of this hyeh
Territory has a right.

2492
02:14:06,860 --> 02:14:10,663
But I’ll tell yu’ this:
a middlin’ doctor is a pore thing,

2493
02:14:10,663 --> 02:14:14,974
and a middlin’ lawyer is a pore thing;
but keep me from a middlin’ man of God.”

2494
02:14:14,974 --> 02:14:18,531
Once again he had reduced it,
but I did not laugh this time.

2495
02:14:18,531 --> 02:14:25,760
I thought there should in truth be heavy
damages for malpractice on human souls.

2496
02:14:25,760 --> 02:14:30,431
But the hot glow of his words,
and the vision of his deepest inner man

2497
02:14:30,431 --> 02:14:33,530
it revealed, faded away abruptly.

2498
02:14:33,530 --> 02:14:36,660
“What do yu’ make of the
proposition yondeh?”

2499
02:14:36,660 --> 02:14:40,432
As he pointed to the cause of this
question he had become again his

2500
02:14:40,432 --> 02:14:43,685
daily, engaging, saturnine self.

2501
02:14:43,685 --> 02:14:48,400
Then I saw over in a fenced meadow,
to which we were now close,

2502
02:14:48,400 --> 02:14:51,096
what he was pleased to
call “the proposition.”

2503
02:14:51,096 --> 02:14:56,944
Proposition in the West does,
in fact, mean whatever you at the moment

2504
02:14:56,944 --> 02:15:01,398
please⁠—an offer to sell you a mine,
a cloudburst, a glass

2505
02:15:01,398 --> 02:15:05,052
of whiskey, a steamboat.

2506
02:15:05,052 --> 02:15:10,904
This time it meant a stranger clad in
black, and of a clerical deportment

2507
02:15:10,904 --> 02:15:16,463
which would in that atmosphere and to a
watchful eye be visible for

2508
02:15:16,463 --> 02:15:17,387
a mile or two.

2509
02:15:17,387 --> 02:15:20,863
“I reckoned yu’ hadn’t noticed him,”
was the Virginian’s reply

2510
02:15:20,863 --> 02:15:22,283
to my ejaculation.

2511
02:15:22,283 --> 02:15:23,188
“Yes.

2512
02:15:23,188 --> 02:15:25,650
He set me goin’ on the
subject a while back.

2513
02:15:25,650 --> -1:59:59,000
I expect he is another missionary
to us pore cowboys.

2514
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2515
02:15:29,566 --> 02:15:36,104
I seemed from a hundred yards to feel
the stranger’s forceful personality.

2516
02:15:36,104 --> 02:15:41,703
It was in his walk⁠—I should better say
stalk⁠—as he promenaded along the creek.

2517
02:15:41,703 --> 02:15:45,598
His hands were behind his back,
and there was an air of waiting,

2518
02:15:45,598 --> 02:15:48,150
of displeased waiting, in his movement.

2519
02:15:48,150 --> 02:15:52,184
“Yes, he’ll be a missionary,”
said the Virginian, conclusively;

2520
02:15:52,184 --> 02:15:55,462
and he took to singing,
or rather to whining,

2521
02:15:55,462 --> 02:15:58,942
with his head tilted at an absurd angle
upward at the sky:⁠—

2522
02:15:58,942 --> 02:16:04,143
“ ‘Dar is a big Car’lina nigger,
About de size of dis chile or p’raps a

2523
02:16:04,143 --> 02:16:08,104
little bigger,By de name of Jim Crow.

2524
02:16:08,104 --> 02:16:11,743
Dat what de white folks call him.

2525
02:16:11,743 --> 02:16:17,175
If ever I sees him I ’tends for to maul
him,Just to let de white folks seeSuch

2526
02:16:17,175 --> -1:59:59,000
an animos as heCan’t walk around the
streets and scandalize me.’

2527
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2528
02:16:22,801 --> 02:16:26,886
The lane which was conducting us to the
group of ranch buildings now turned a

2529
02:16:26,886 --> 02:16:30,631
corner of the meadow,
and the Virginian went on

2530
02:16:30,631 --> 02:16:32,056
with his second verse:⁠—

2531
02:16:32,056 --> 02:16:35,535
“ ‘Great big fool, he
hasn’t any knowledge.

2532
02:16:35,535 --> 02:16:36,372
Gosh!

2533
02:16:36,372 --> 02:16:38,434
how could he, when he’s
never been to scollege?

2534
02:16:38,434 --> -1:59:59,000
Neither has I.But I’se come mighty nigh;
I peaked through de door as I went by.’

2535
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2536
02:16:42,797 --> 02:16:46,546
He was beginning a third stanza,
but stopped short; a horse had

