02:16:46,546 --> 02:16:48,177
neighed close behind us.

2538
02:16:48,177 --> 02:16:52,039
“Trampas,” said he, without turning his
head, “we are home.”

2539
02:16:52,039 --> 02:16:53,792
“It looks that way.”

2540
02:16:53,792 --> 02:16:57,232
Some ten yards were between ourselves and
Trampas, where he followed.

2541
02:16:57,232 --> 02:17:01,600
“And I’ll trouble yu’ for my rope yu’
took this mawnin’ instead o’ your own.”

2542
02:17:01,600 --> 02:17:05,265
“I don’t know as it’s your rope I’ve got.”

2543
02:17:05,265 --> 02:17:10,393
Trampas skilfully spoke this so that a
precisely opposite meaning

2544
02:17:10,393 --> 02:17:11,940
flowed from his words.

2545
02:17:11,940 --> 02:17:15,749
If it was discussion he
tried for, he failed.

2546
02:17:15,749 --> 02:17:19,784
The Virginian’s hand moved,
and for one thick, flashing moment my

2547
02:17:19,784 --> 02:17:23,118
thoughts were evidently also
the thoughts of Trampas.

2548
02:17:23,118 --> 02:17:27,899
But the Virginian only held out to
Trampas the rope which he had

2549
02:17:27,899 --> 02:17:29,502
detached from his saddle.

2550
02:17:29,502 --> 02:17:36,953
“Take your hand off your gun, Trampas.

2551
02:17:36,953 --> 02:17:41,257
If I had wanted to kill yu’ you’d be
lying nine days back on the road now.

2552
02:17:41,257 --> 02:17:42,841
Here’s your rope.

2553
02:17:42,841 --> 02:17:44,659
Did yu’ expect I’d not know it?

2554
02:17:44,659 --> 02:17:48,740
It’s the only one in camp the stiffness
