2573
02:18:52,916 --> 02:18:58,283
explanatory⁠—“the ropes was all strewed
round camp, and in the hustle I⁠—”

2574
02:18:58,283 --> 02:19:03,170
“Pardon me,” said a sonorous voice behind
us, “do you happen to

2575
02:19:03,170 --> 02:19:05,676
have seen Judge Henry?”

2576
02:19:05,676 --> 02:19:11,532
It was the reverend gentleman in his
meadow, come to the fence.

2577
02:19:11,532 --> 02:19:18,608
As we turned round to him he spoke on,
with much rotund authority in his eye.

2578
02:19:18,608 --> 02:19:22,866
“From his answer to my letter,
Judge Henry undoubtedly expects me here.

2579
02:19:22,866 --> 02:19:28,460
I have arrived from Fetterman according
to my plan which I announced to him,

2580
02:19:28,460 --> 02:19:32,913
to find that he has been absent all
day⁠—absent the whole day.”

2581
02:19:32,913 --> 02:19:39,120
The Virginian sat sidewise to talk,
one long, straight leg supporting him on

2582
02:19:39,120 --> 02:19:43,912
one stirrup, the other bent at ease,
the boot half lifted

2583
02:19:43,912 --> 02:19:45,460
from its dangling stirrup.

2584
02:19:45,460 --> 02:19:48,781
He made himself the perfection
of courtesy.

2585
02:19:48,781 --> 02:19:51,903
“The Judge is frequently
absent all night, seh.”

2586
02:19:51,903 --> 02:19:53,663
“Scarcely tonight, I think.

2587
02:19:53,663 --> 02:19:56,001
I thought you might know
something about him.”

2588
02:19:56,001 --> 02:19:58,705
“I have been absent myself, seh.”

2589
02:19:58,705 --> 02:19:59,310
“Ah!

2590
02:19:59,310 --> 02:20:01,466
On a vacation, perhaps?”

2591
02:20:01,466 --> 02:20:03,759
The divine had a ruddy facet.

2592
02:20:03,759 --> 02:20:09,577
His strong glance was straight and frank
and fearless; but his smile too much

2593
02:20:09,577 --> 02:20:14,417
reminded me of days bygone,
when we used to return to school from

2594
02:20:14,417 --> 02:20:18,008
the Christmas holidays,
and the masters would shake our hands

2595
02:20:18,008 --> 02:20:21,476
and welcome us with:
“Robert, John, Edward,

2596
02:20:21,476 --> 02:20:24,273
glad to see you all looking so well!

2597
02:20:24,273 --> 02:20:27,547
Rested, and ready for
hard work, I’m sure!”

2598
02:20:27,547 --> 02:20:31,873
That smile does not really please even
good, tame little boys;

2599
02:20:31,873 --> 02:20:34,026
and the Virginian was nearing thirty.

2600
02:20:34,026 --> 02:20:37,026
“It has not been vacation this trip,
seh,” said he, settling

2601
02:20:37,026 --> 02:20:38,547
straight in his saddle.

2602
02:20:38,547 --> 02:20:42,546
“There’s the Judge driving in now,
in time for all questions yu’

2603
02:20:42,546 --> 02:20:43,401
have to ask him.”

2604
02:20:43,401 --> 02:20:46,456
His horse took a step,
but was stopped short.

2605
02:20:46,456 --> 02:20:49,806
There lay the Virginian’s
rope on the ground.

2606
02:20:49,806 --> 02:20:54,366
I had been aware of Trampas’s quite
proper departure during the talk;

2607
02:20:54,366 --> 02:21:00,030
and as he was leaving,
I seemed also to be aware of his placing

2608
02:21:00,030 --> 02:21:03,649
the coil across the cantle
of its owner’s saddle.

2609
02:21:03,649 --> 02:21:06,350
Had he intended it to fall and have
