2640
02:22:54,221 --> 02:22:58,510
But I did not know, and I
spoke with innocent cheeriness.

2641
02:22:58,510 --> 02:23:00,880
“Is the parson going to save us?”

2642
02:23:00,880 --> 02:23:03,904
I asked; and I fairly
jumped at his voice:⁠—

2643
02:23:03,904 --> 02:23:05,435
“Don’t talk so much!”

2644
02:23:05,435 --> 02:23:06,265
he burst out.

2645
02:23:06,265 --> 02:23:09,714
I had got the whole accumulation!

2646
02:23:09,714 --> 02:23:11,074
“Who’s been talking?”

2647
02:23:11,074 --> 02:23:13,677
I in equal anger screeched back.

2648
02:23:13,677 --> 02:23:15,325
“I’m not trying to save you.

2649
02:23:15,325 --> 02:23:16,611
I didn’t take your rope.”

2650
02:23:16,611 --> 02:23:20,274
And having poured this out,
I whipped up my pony.

2651
02:23:20,274 --> 02:23:23,777
But he spurred his own alongside of me;
and glancing at him,

2652
02:23:23,777 --> 02:23:26,970
I saw that he was now
convulsed with internal mirth.

2653
02:23:26,970 --> 02:23:32,119
I therefore drew down to a walk,
and he straightened into gravity.

2654
02:23:32,119 --> 02:23:36,718
“I’m right obliged to yu’,” he laid his
hand in its buckskin gauntlet upon my

2655
02:23:36,718 --> 02:23:40,118
horse’s mane as he spoke,
“for bringing me back out o’ my

2656
02:23:40,118 --> 02:23:41,184
nonsense.

2657
02:23:41,184 --> 02:23:44,417
I’ll be as serene as a bird
now⁠—whatever they do.

2658
02:23:44,417 --> 02:23:48,848
A man,” he stated reflectively,
“any full-sized man,

2659
02:23:48,848 --> 02:23:50,914
ought to own a big lot of temper.

2660
02:23:50,914 --> 02:23:55,674
And like all his valuable possessions,
