promised, and was sentimentally
continuing:⁠—

2672
02:24:34,725 --> 02:24:40,686
“ ‘De sun is made of mud from de bottom
of de river;De moon is made o’ fox-fire,

2673
02:24:40,686 --> 02:24:44,510
as you might disciver;
De stars like de ladies’ eyes,

2674
02:24:44,510 --> 02:24:48,460
All round de world dey flies,
To give a little light when

2675
02:24:48,460 --> -1:59:59,000
de moon don’t rise.’

2676
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2677
02:24:50,240 --> 02:24:55,025
If words were meant to conceal our
thoughts, melody is perhaps a still

2678
02:24:55,025 --> 02:24:56,145
thicker veil for them.

2679
02:24:56,145 --> 02:25:01,401
Whatever temper he had lost,
he had certainly found again;

2680
02:25:01,401 --> 02:25:06,716
but this all the more fitted him to deal
with Trampas, when the

2681
02:25:06,716 --> 02:25:08,625
dealing should begin.

2682
02:25:08,625 --> 02:25:12,778
I had half a mind to speak to the Judge,
only it seemed beyond

2683
02:25:12,778 --> 02:25:14,730
a mere visitor’s business.

2684
02:25:14,730 --> 02:25:19,409
Our missionary was at this moment himself
speaking to Judge Henry at the door

2685
02:25:19,409 --> 02:25:20,670
of the home ranch.

2686
02:25:20,670 --> 02:25:23,590
“I reckon he’s explaining
he has been awaiting.”

