They were delighted to have us,
but they hadn’t foreseen that we

2758
02:29:25,056 --> 02:29:26,947
should all be simultaneous.

2759
02:29:26,947 --> 02:29:30,718
The foreman’s house had been prepared for
two of us, and did we mind?

2760
02:29:30,718 --> 02:29:35,524
The two of us were Dr. MacBride and
myself; and I expected him to mind.

2761
02:29:35,524 --> 02:29:37,079
But I wronged him grossly.

2762
02:29:37,079 --> 02:29:40,159
It would be much better,
he assured Mrs. Henry,

2763
02:29:40,159 --> 02:29:45,187
than straw in a stable,
which he had tried several times,

2764
02:29:45,187 --> 02:29:46,853
and was quite ready for.

2765
02:29:46,853 --> 02:29:52,692
So I saw that though he kept his vigorous
body clean when he could,

2766
02:29:52,692 --> 02:29:56,222
he cared nothing for it in the
face of his mission.

2767
02:29:56,222 --> 02:29:59,607
How the foreman and his wife relished
being turned out during a week for a

2768
02:29:59,607 --> 02:30:03,847
missionary and myself was not my
concern, although while he and I made

2769
02:30:03,847 --> 02:30:07,355
ready for supper over there,
it struck me as hard on them.

2770
02:30:07,355 --> 02:30:10,883
The room with its two cots and furniture
was as nice as possible;

2771
02:30:10,883 --> 02:30:14,532
and we closed the door upon the
adjoining room, which,

2772
02:30:14,532 --> 02:30:17,723
however, seemed also untenanted.

2773
02:30:17,723 --> 02:30:18,203
Mrs.

2774
02:30:18,203 --> 02:30:23,325
Henry gave us a meal so good that I have
remembered it, and her husband the Judge

2775
02:30:23,325 --> 02:30:26,838
strove his best that we should
eat it in merriment.

2776
02:30:26,838 --> 02:30:30,598
He poured out his anecdotes like wine,
and we should have quickly warmed to

2777
02:30:30,598 --> 02:30:37,319
them; but Dr. MacBride sat among us,
giving occasional heavy ha-ha’s,

2778
02:30:37,319 --> 02:30:41,726
which produced, as Miss Molly Wood
whispered to me, a “dreadfully

2779
02:30:41,726 --> 02:30:43,914
cavernous effect.”

2780
02:30:43,914 --> 02:30:47,931
Was it his sermon, we wondered,
that he was thinking over?

2781
02:30:47,931 --> 02:30:52,531
I told her of the copious sheaf of them I
had seen him pull from his wallet

2782
02:30:52,531 --> 02:30:54,072
over at the foreman’s.

2783
02:30:54,072 --> 02:30:55,237
“Goodness!”

2784
02:30:55,237 --> 02:30:56,059
said she.

2785
02:30:56,059 --> 02:30:57,856
“Then are we to hear one every evening?”

2786
02:30:57,856 --> 02:31:01,670
This I doubted; he had probably been
picking one out suitable

2787
02:31:01,670 --> 02:31:02,641
for the occasion.

2788
02:31:02,641 --> 02:31:06,430
“Putting his best foot foremost,”
was her comment; “I suppose they have

2789
02:31:06,430 --> 02:31:08,890
best feet, like the rest of us.”

2790
02:31:08,890 --> 02:31:11,181
Then she grew delightfully sharp.

2791
02:31:11,181 --> 02:31:16,174
“Do you know, when I first heard him I
thought his voice was hearty.

2792
02:31:16,174 --> 02:31:20,518
But if you listen, you’ll
find it’s merely militant.

2793
02:31:20,518 --> 02:31:22,639
He never really meets you with it.

2794
02:31:22,639 --> -1:59:59,000
He’s off on his hill watching the
battlefield the whole time.

2795
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2796
02:31:25,442 --> 02:31:27,357
“He will find a hardened pagan here.”

2797
02:31:27,357 --> 02:31:28,171
“Judge Henry?”

2798
02:31:28,171 --> 02:31:29,800
“Oh, no!

2799
02:31:29,800 --> 02:31:33,699
The wild man you’re taming brought
you Kenilworth safe back.”

2800
02:31:33,699 --> 02:31:34,779
She was smooth.

2801
02:31:34,779 --> 02:31:37,019
“Oh, as for taming him!

2802
02:31:37,019 --> 02:31:39,500
But don’t you find him intelligent?”

2803
02:31:39,500 --> 02:31:43,124
Suddenly I somehow knew that she didn’t
want to tame him.

2804
02:31:43,124 --> 02:31:45,380
But what did she want to do?

2805
02:31:45,380 --> 02:31:48,090
The thought of her had made
him blush this afternoon.

2806
02:31:48,090 --> 02:31:51,950
No thought of him made
her blush this evening.

2807
02:31:51,950 --> 02:31:56,953
A great laugh from the rest of the
company made me aware that the Judge had

2808
02:31:56,953 --> 02:32:00,063
consummated his tale
of the “Sole Survivor.”

2809
02:32:00,063 --> 02:32:04,903
“And so,” he finished,
“they all went off as mad as hops

2810
02:32:04,903 --> 02:32:07,112
because it hadn’t been a massacre.”

2811
02:32:07,112 --> 02:32:13,627
Mr. and Mrs. Ogden⁠—they were the New
Yorkers⁠—gave this story much applause,

2812
02:32:13,627 --> 02:32:20,362
and Dr. MacBride half a minute later
laid his “ha-ha,” like a heavy

2813
02:32:20,362 --> 02:32:22,572
stone, upon the gaiety.

2814
02:32:22,572 --> 02:32:27,244
“I’ll never be able to stand seven
sermons,” said Miss Wood to me.

2815
02:32:27,244 --> 02:32:30,645
“Talking of massacres,”
⁠—I now hastened to address the already

2816
02:32:30,645 --> 02:32:34,128
saddened table⁠—“I have
recently escaped one myself.”

2817
02:32:34,128 --> 02:32:36,483
The Judge had come to an
end of his powers.

2818
02:32:36,483 --> 02:32:37,877
“Oh, tell us!”

2819
02:32:37,877 --> 02:32:38,847
he implored.

2820
02:32:38,847 --> 02:32:44,629
“Seriously, sir, I think we grazed pretty
wet tragedy but your extraordinary man

2821
02:32:44,629 --> 02:32:46,886
brought us out into comedy safe and
dry.”

2822
02:32:46,886 --> 02:32:50,932
This gave me their attention;
and, from that afternoon in Dakota when

2823
02:32:50,932 --> 02:32:55,494
I had first stepped aboard the caboose,
I told them the whole tale of my

2824
02:32:55,494 --> 02:33:00,038
experience: how I grew immediately aware
that all was not right,

2825
02:33:00,038 --> 02:33:05,450
by the Virginian’s kicking the cook off
the train; how, as we journeyed,

2826
02:33:05,450 --> 02:33:08,390
the dark bubble of mutiny swelled hourly
beneath my eyes; and how,

2827
02:33:08,390 --> 02:33:12,310
when it was threatening I know not what
explosion, the Virginian had pricked it

2828
02:33:12,310 --> 02:33:16,069
with humor, so that it burst in
nothing but harmless laughter.

2829
02:33:16,069 --> 02:33:20,711
Their eyes followed my narrative:
the New Yorkers, because such events do

2830
02:33:20,711 --> 02:33:25,351
not happen upon the shores of the
Hudson; Mrs. Henry, because she was my

2831
02:33:25,351 --> 02:33:29,545
hostess; Miss Wood followed for whatever
her reasons were⁠—I

2832
02:33:29,545 --> 02:33:36,044
couldn’t see her eyes;
rather, I felther listening intently to

2833
02:33:36,044 --> 02:33:40,987
the deeds and dangers of the man she
didn’t care to tame.

2834
02:33:40,987 --> 02:33:46,747
But it was the eyes of the Judge and the
missionary which I saw riveted upon me

2835
02:33:46,747 --> 02:33:51,031
indeed until the end;
and they forthwith made plain

2836
02:33:51,031 --> 02:33:53,071
their quite dissimilar opinions.

2837
02:33:53,071 --> 02:33:56,808
Judge Henry struck the table
lightly with his fist.

2838
02:33:56,808 --> 02:33:57,738
“I knew it!”

2839
02:33:57,738 --> 02:34:01,331
And he leaned back in his chair with
a face of contentment.

2840
02:34:01,331 --> 02:34:06,447
He had trusted his man,
and his man had proved worthy.

2841
02:34:06,447 --> 02:34:07,352
“Pardon me.”

2842
02:34:07,352 --> 02:34:07,992
Dr.

2843
02:34:07,992 --> 02:34:13,627
MacBride had a manner of saying “pardon
me,” which rendered forgiveness

2844
02:34:13,627 --> 02:34:15,930
well-nigh impossible.

2845
02:34:15,930 --> 02:34:19,827
The Judge waited for him.

2846
02:34:19,827 --> 02:34:24,440
“Am I to understand that these⁠—a⁠—
cowboys attempted to mutiny,

2847
02:34:24,440 --> 02:34:28,528
and were discouraged in this attempt
upon finding themselves less skilful at

2848
02:34:28,528 --> 02:34:31,796
lying than the man they
had plotted to depose?”

2849
02:34:31,796 --> 02:34:32,923
I began an answer.

2850
02:34:32,923 --> 02:34:37,086
“It was other qualities,
sir, that happened to be revealed and

2851
02:34:37,086 --> 02:34:40,046
asserted by what you
call his lying that⁠—”

2852
02:34:40,046 --> 02:34:43,381
“And what am I to call it,
if it is not lying?

2853
02:34:43,381 --> 02:34:48,219
A competition in deceit in which,
I admit, he out did them.

2854
02:34:48,219 --> 02:34:49,696
“It’s their way to⁠—”

2855
02:34:49,696 --> 02:34:50,655
“Pardon me.

2856
02:34:50,655 --> 02:34:51,892
Their way to lie?

2857
02:34:51,892 --> 02:34:54,633
They bow down to the greatest in this?”

2858
02:34:54,633 --> 02:34:57,352
“Oh,” said Miss Wood in my
ear, “give him up.”

2859
02:34:57,352 --> 02:34:58,595
The Judge took a turn.

2860
02:34:58,595 --> 02:35:01,365
“We-ell, Doctor⁠—” He
seemed to stick here.

2861
02:35:01,365 --> 02:35:01,799
Mr.

2862
02:35:01,799 --> 02:35:04,843
Ogden handsomely assisted him.

2863
02:35:04,843 --> 02:35:07,803
“You’ve said the word yourself, Doctor.

2864
02:35:07,803 --> 02:35:10,571
It’s the competition, don’t you see?

2865
02:35:10,571 --> 02:35:13,403
The trial of strength by
no matter what test.”

2866
02:35:13,403 --> 02:35:17,076
“Yes,” said Miss Wood, unexpectedly.

2867
02:35:17,076 --> 02:35:21,874
“And it wasn’t that George Washington
couldn’t tell a lie.

2868
02:35:21,874 --> 02:35:23,171
He just wouldn’t.

2869
02:35:23,171 --> 02:35:27,702
I’m sure if he’d undertaken to he’d have
told a much better one than Cornwall’s.”

2870
02:35:27,702 --> 02:35:28,822
“Ha-ha, madam!

2871
02:35:28,822 --> 02:35:31,853
You draw an ingenious
subtlety from your books.”

2872
02:35:31,853 --> 02:35:34,903
“It’s all plain to me,” Ogden pursued.

2873
02:35:34,903 --> 02:35:36,426
“The men were morose.

2874
02:35:36,426 --> 02:35:38,750
This foreman was in the minority.

2875
02:35:38,750 --> 02:35:43,374
He cajoled them into a bout of tall
stories, and told the tallest himself.

2876
02:35:43,374 --> 02:35:47,413
And when they found they had swallowed it
whole⁠—well, it would certainly take the

2877
02:35:47,413 --> 02:35:49,925
starch out of me,” he concluded.

2878
02:35:49,925 --> 02:35:52,208
“I couldn’t be a serious
mutineer after that.”

2879
02:35:52,208 --> 02:35:52,725
Dr.

2880
02:35:52,725 --> 02:35:54,955
MacBride now sounded his strongest bass.

2881
02:35:54,955 --> 02:35:56,065
“Pardon me.

2882
02:35:56,065 --> 02:35:58,614
I cannot accept such a view, sir.

2883
02:35:58,614 --> 02:36:02,955
There is a levity abroad in our land
which I must deplore.

2884
02:36:02,955 --> 02:36:07,539
No matter how leniently you may try to
put it, in the end we have the spectacle

2885
02:36:07,539 --> 02:36:13,594
of a struggle between men where lying
decides the survival of the fittest.

2886
02:36:13,594 --> 02:36:18,072
Better, far better, if it was to come,
that they had shot honest bullets.

2887
02:36:18,072 --> 02:36:20,290
There are worse evils than war.”

2888
02:36:20,290 --> 02:36:22,776
The Doctor’s eye glared
righteously about him.

2889
02:36:22,776 --> 02:36:26,522
None of us, I think, trembled;
or, if we did, it was with

2890
02:36:26,522 --> 02:36:29,454
emotions other than fear.

2891
02:36:29,454 --> 02:36:29,736
Mrs.

2892
02:36:29,736 --> 02:36:35,379
Henry at once introduced the subject of
trout-fishing, and thus happily removed

2893
02:36:35,379 --> 02:36:39,321
us from the edge of whatever sort of
precipice we seemed to have approached;

2894
02:36:39,321 --> 02:36:41,949
for Dr. MacBride had brought his rod.

2895
02:36:41,949 --> 02:36:46,919
He dilated upon this sport with fervor,
and we assured him that the streams upon

2896
02:36:46,919 --> 02:36:51,807
the west slope of the Bow Leg Mountains
would afford him plenty of it.

2897
02:36:51,807 --> 02:36:56,618
Thus we ended our meal
in carefully preserved amity.

2898
02:36:56,618 --> 02:36:57,943
CHAPTER XX

2899
02:36:57,943 --> 02:37:00,533
The Judge Ignores Particulars

2900
02:37:00,533 --> 02:37:03,633
“Do you often have these visitations?”

2901
02:37:03,633 --> 02:37:05,901
Ogden inquired of Judge Henry.

2902
02:37:05,901 --> 02:37:09,792
Our host was giving us whiskey in his
office, and Dr. MacBride,

2903
02:37:09,792 --> 02:37:14,450
while we smoked apart from the ladies,
had repaired to his quarters in the

2904
02:37:14,450 --> 02:37:18,809
foreman’s house previous to the service
which he was shortly to hold.

2905
02:37:18,809 --> 02:37:20,067
The Judge laughed.

2906
02:37:20,067 --> 02:37:22,996
“They come now and then through the year.

2907
02:37:22,996 --> 02:37:24,649
I like the bishop to come.

2908
02:37:24,649 --> 02:37:26,826
And the men always like it.

2909
02:37:26,826 --> 02:37:30,002
But I fear our friend will scarcely
please them so well.”

2910
02:37:30,002 --> 02:37:31,316
“You don’t mean they’ll⁠—”

2911
02:37:31,316 --> 02:37:32,039
“Oh, no.

2912
02:37:32,039 --> 02:37:33,440
They’ll keep quiet.

2913
02:37:33,440 --> 02:37:39,289
The fact is, they have a good deal better
manners than he has, if he only knew it.

2914
02:37:39,289 --> 02:37:41,042
They’ll be able to bear him.

2915
02:37:41,042 --> 02:37:42,609
But as for any good he’ll do⁠—”

2916
02:37:42,609 --> 02:37:47,290
“I doubt if he knows a word of science,”
said I, musing about the Doctor.

2917
02:37:47,290 --> 02:37:48,639
“Science!

2918
02:37:48,639 --> 02:37:52,043
He doesn’t know what Christianity is yet.

2919
02:37:52,043 --> 02:37:55,486
I’ve entertained many guests,
but none⁠—The whole secret,”

2920
02:37:55,486 --> 02:37:59,407
broke off Judge Henry,
“lies in the way you treat people.

2921
02:37:59,407 --> 02:38:03,133
As soon as you treat men as your
brothers, they are ready to acknowledge

2922
02:38:03,133 --> 02:38:06,574
you⁠—if you deserve it⁠—
as their superior.

2923
02:38:06,574 --> 02:38:10,537
That’s the whole bottom of Christianity,
and that’s what our missionary

2924
02:38:10,537 --> -1:59:59,000
will never know.

2925
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2926
02:38:11,513 --> 02:38:16,010
There was a somewhat heavy knock at the
office door, and I think we all feared

2927
02:38:16,010 --> 02:38:17,561
it was Dr. MacBride.

2928
02:38:17,561 --> 02:38:21,074
But when the Judge opened,
the Virginian was standing

2929
02:38:21,074 --> 02:38:22,414
there in the darkness.

2930
02:38:22,414 --> 02:38:23,153
“So!”

2931
02:38:23,153 --> 02:38:25,166
The Judge opened the door wide.

2932
02:38:25,166 --> 02:38:30,037
He was very hearty to the
man he had trusted.

2933
02:38:30,037 --> 02:38:32,877
“You’re back at last.”

2934
02:38:32,877 --> 02:38:34,981
“I came to repawt.”

2935
02:38:34,981 --> 02:38:38,026
While they shook hands, Ogden nudged me.

2936
02:38:38,026 --> 02:38:38,982
“That the fellow?”

2937
02:38:38,982 --> 02:38:39,910
I nodded.

2938
02:38:39,910 --> 02:38:42,631
“Fellow who kicked the
cook off the train?”

2939
02:38:42,631 --> 02:38:47,436
I again nodded, and he looked at the
Virginian, his eye and his stature.

2940
02:38:47,436 --> 02:38:52,244
Judge Henry, properly democratic,
now introduced him to Ogden.

2941
02:38:52,244 --> 02:38:57,480
The New Yorker also meant
to be properly democratic.

2942
02:38:57,480 --> -1:59:59,000
“You’re the man I’ve been hearing
such a lot about.

2943
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2944
02:39:00,675 --> 02:39:04,332
But familiarity is not equality.

2945
02:39:04,332 --> 02:39:09,645
“Then I expect yu’ have the advantage of
me, seh,” said the Virginian,

2946
02:39:09,645 --> 02:39:11,427
very politely.

2947
02:39:11,427 --> 02:39:13,038
“Shall I repawt tomorro’?”

2948
02:39:13,038 --> 02:39:15,496
His grave eyes were on the Judge again.

2949
02:39:15,496 --> 02:39:21,133
Of me he had taken no notice;
he had come as an employee

2950
02:39:21,133 --> 02:39:22,780
to see his employer.

2951
02:39:22,780 --> 02:39:26,012
“Yes, yes; I’ll want to hear
about the cattle tomorrow.

2952
02:39:26,012 --> 02:39:28,415
But step inside a moment now.

2953
02:39:28,415 --> 02:39:33,305
There’s a matter⁠—” The Virginian stepped
inside, and took off his hat.

2954
02:39:33,305 --> 02:39:35,236
“Sit down.

2955
02:39:35,236 --> 02:39:39,156
You had trouble⁠—I’ve heard something
about it,” the Judge went on.

2956
02:39:39,156 --> 02:39:43,041
The Virginian sat down,
grave and graceful.

2957
02:39:43,041 --> 02:39:45,439
But he held the brim of his
hat all the while.

2958
02:39:45,439 --> 02:39:49,261
He looked at Ogden and me,
and then back at his employer.

2959
02:39:49,261 --> 02:39:51,308
There was reluctance in his eye.

2960
02:39:51,308 --> 02:39:54,937
I wondered if his employer could be going
to make him tell his own exploits in the

2961
02:39:54,937 --> 02:39:58,669
presence of us outsiders;
and there came into my memory the Bengal

2962
02:39:58,669 --> 02:40:01,295
tiger at a trained-animal show
I had once seen.

2963
02:40:01,295 --> 02:40:03,911
“You had some trouble,”
repeated the Judge.

2964
02:40:03,911 --> 02:40:08,834
“Well, there was a time when they maybe
wanted to have notions.

2965
02:40:08,834 --> 02:40:10,077
They’re good boys.”

2966
02:40:10,077 --> 02:40:12,884
And he smiled a very little.

2967
02:40:12,884 --> 02:40:16,492
Contentment increased in the Judge’s face.

2968
02:40:16,492 --> -1:59:59,000
“Trampas a good boy too?

2969
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2970
02:40:18,173 --> 02:40:22,483
But this time the Bengal
tiger did not smile.

2971
02:40:22,483 --> 02:40:25,462
He sat with his eye fastened
on his employer.

2972
02:40:25,462 --> 02:40:28,736
The Judge passed rather quickly on
to his next point.

2973
02:40:28,736 --> 02:40:31,843
“You’ve brought them all back,
though, I understand,

2974
02:40:31,843 --> 02:40:34,862
safe and sound, without a scratch?”

2975
02:40:34,862 --> 02:40:40,057
The Virginian looked down at his hat,
then up again at the Judge, mildly.

2976
02:40:40,057 --> 02:40:41,653
“I had to part with my cook.”

2977
02:40:41,653 --> 02:40:45,930
There was no use; Ogden
and myself exploded.

2978
02:40:45,930 --> 02:40:50,862
Even upon the embarrassed Virginian a
large grin slowly forced itself.

2979
02:40:50,862 --> 02:40:53,380
“I guess yu’ know about it,” he murmured.

2980
02:40:53,380 --> 02:40:56,970
And he looked at me with
a sort of reproach.

2981
02:40:56,970 --> 02:41:01,281
He knew it was I who had told
tales out of school.

2982
02:41:01,281 --> 02:41:05,332
“I only want to say,”
said Ogden, conciliatingly,

2983
02:41:05,332 --> 02:41:07,891
“that I know I couldn’t
have handled those men.”

2984
02:41:07,891 --> 02:41:09,133
The Virginian relented.

2985
02:41:09,133 --> 02:41:11,574
“Yu’ never tried, seh.”

2986
02:41:11,574 --> 02:41:16,104
The Judge had remained serious;
but he showed himself plainly

2987
02:41:16,104 --> 02:41:17,782
more and more contented.

2988
02:41:17,782 --> 02:41:19,719
“Quite right,” he said.

2989
02:41:19,719 --> 02:41:22,185
“You had to part with your cook.

2990
02:41:22,185 --> 02:41:25,597
When I put a man in charge,
I put him in charge.

2991
02:41:25,597 --> 02:41:28,439
I don’t make particulars my business.

2992
02:41:28,439 --> 02:41:31,994
They’re to be always his.

2993
02:41:31,994 --> -1:59:59,000
Do you understand?

2994
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2995
02:41:34,770 --> 02:41:35,553
“Thank yu’.”

2996
02:41:35,553 --> 02:41:39,393
The Virginian understood that his
employer was praising his

2997
02:41:39,393 --> 02:41:41,192
management of the expedition.

2998
02:41:41,192 --> 02:41:46,395
But I don’t think he at all discerned⁠—as
I did presently⁠—that his employer had

2999
02:41:46,395 --> 02:41:50,626
just been putting him to a further test,
had laid before him the temptation of

3000
02:41:50,626 --> 02:41:54,804
complaining of a fellow-workman and
blowing his own trumpet,

3001
02:41:54,804 --> 02:41:58,280
and was delighted with his reticence.

3002
02:41:58,280 --> 02:42:00,505
He made a movement to rise.

3003
02:42:00,505 --> 02:42:04,073
“I haven’t finished,” said the Judge.

3004
02:42:04,073 --> 02:42:07,727
“I was coming to the matter.

3005
02:42:07,727 --> 02:42:12,808
There’s one particular⁠—since I do happen
to have been told.

3006
02:42:12,808 --> 02:42:16,340
I fancy Trampas has learned
something he didn’t expect.”

3007
02:42:16,340 --> 02:42:22,408
This time the Virginian evidently did not
understand, any more than I did.

3008
02:42:22,408 --> 02:42:26,974
One hand played with his hat,
mechanically turning it round.

3009
02:42:26,974 --> 02:42:28,977
The Judge explained.

3010
02:42:28,977 --> 02:42:31,366
“I mean about Roberts.”

3011
02:42:31,366 --> 02:42:36,098
A pulse of triumph shot over the
Southerner’s face, turning it savage

3012
02:42:36,098 --> 02:42:37,613
for that fleeting instant.

3013
02:42:37,613 --> 02:42:41,277
He understood now, and was unable to
suppress this much answer.

3014
02:42:41,277 --> 02:42:42,657
But he was silent.

3015
02:42:42,657 --> 02:42:46,536
“You see,” the Judge explained to me,
“I was obliged to let Roberts,

3016
02:42:46,536 --> 02:42:49,112
my old foreman, go last week.

3017
02:42:49,112 --> 02:42:52,504
His wife could not have stood another
winter here, and a good position was

3018
02:42:52,504 --> 02:42:54,500
offered to him near Los Angeles.”

3019
02:42:54,500 --> 02:42:55,355
I did see.

3020
02:42:55,355 --> 02:42:57,435
I saw a number of things.

3021
02:42:57,435 --> 02:43:02,246
I saw why the foreman’s house had been
empty to receive Dr. MacBride and me.

3022
02:43:02,246 --> 02:43:06,351
And I saw that the Judge had
been very clever indeed.

3023
02:43:06,351 --> 02:43:10,200
For I had abstained from telling any
tales about the present feeling between

3024
02:43:10,200 --> 02:43:12,401
Trampas and the Virginian;
but he had divined it.

3025
02:43:12,401 --> 02:43:14,959
Well enough for him to say that
“particulars” were something he let

3026
02:43:14,959 --> 02:43:15,659
alone

3027
02:43:15,659 --> 02:43:18,799
; he evidently kept a deep eye on the
undercurrents at his ranch.

3028
02:43:18,799 --> 02:43:22,841
He knew that in Roberts,
Trampas had lost a powerful friend.

3029
02:43:22,841 --> 02:43:28,413
And this was what I most saw,
this final fact, that Trampas had no

3030
02:43:28,413 --> 02:43:30,255
longer any intervening shield.

3031
02:43:30,255 --> 02:43:33,953
He and the Virginian stood
indeed man to man.

3032
02:43:33,953 --> 02:43:39,434
“And so,” the Judge continued speaking to
me, “here I am at a very inconvenient

3033
02:43:39,434 --> 02:43:40,834
time without a foreman.

3034
02:43:40,834 --> 02:43:44,882
Unless,” I caught the twinkle in his eyes
before he turned to the Virginian,

3035
02:43:44,882 --> 02:43:47,637
“unless you’re willing to
take the position yourself.

3036
02:43:47,637 --> 02:43:48,411
Will you?”

3037
02:43:48,411 --> 02:43:53,358
I saw the Southerner’s hand grip his hat
as he was turning it round.

3038
02:43:53,358 --> 02:43:56,566
He held it still now,
and his other hand found it and

3039
02:43:56,566 --> 02:43:59,086
gradually crumpled the soft crown in.

3040
02:43:59,086 --> 02:44:02,401
It meant everything to him:
recognition, higher station,

3041
02:44:02,401 --> 02:44:08,462
better fortune, a separate house of his
own, and⁠—perhaps⁠—one step nearer to

3042
02:44:08,462 --> 02:44:09,567
the woman he wanted.

3043
02:44:09,567 --> 02:44:15,287
I don’t know what words he might have
said to the Judge had they been alone,

3044
02:44:15,287 --> 02:44:19,566
but the Judge had chosen to do it in our
presence, the whole thing

3045
02:44:19,566 --> 02:44:22,402
from beginning to end.

3046
02:44:22,402 --> 02:44:26,231
The Virginian sat with the damp coming
out on his forehead,

3047
02:44:26,231 --> 02:44:29,193
and his eyes dropped from his
employer’s.

3048
02:44:29,193 --> 02:44:32,901
“Thank yu’,” was what he managed
at last to say.

3049
02:44:32,901 --> 02:44:36,488
“Well, now, I’m greatly relieved!”

3050
02:44:36,488 --> 02:44:39,567
exclaimed the Judge, rising at once.

3051
02:44:39,567 --> 02:44:42,273
He spoke with haste, and lightly.

3052
02:44:42,273 --> 02:44:44,123
“That’s excellent.

3053
02:44:44,123 --> 02:44:47,778
I was in some thing of a hole,”
he said to Ogden and me;

3054
02:44:47,778 --> 02:44:50,116
“and this gives me one thing
less to think of.

3055
02:44:50,116 --> 02:44:54,908
Saves me a lot of particulars,”
he jocosely added to the Virginian,

3056
02:44:54,908 --> 02:44:56,664
who was now also standing up.

3057
02:44:56,664 --> 02:44:58,116
“Begin right off.

3058
02:44:58,116 --> 02:44:59,995
Leave the bunk house.

3059
02:44:59,995 --> 02:45:03,190
The gentlemen won’t mind your sleeping
in your own house.”

3060
02:45:03,190 --> 02:45:05,510
Thus he dismissed his new foreman gayly.

3061
02:45:05,510 --> 02:45:10,825
But the new foreman, when he got outside,
turned back for one gruff word⁠—“I’ll

3062
02:45:10,825 --> 02:45:12,825
try to please yu’.”

3063
02:45:12,825 --> 02:45:14,144
That was all.

3064
02:45:14,144 --> 02:45:16,432
He was gone in the darkness.

3065
02:45:16,432 --> 02:45:20,508
But there was light enough for me,
looking after him, to see him lay his

3066
02:45:20,508 --> 02:45:24,926
hand on a shoulder-high gate and vault
it as if he had been the wind.

3067
02:45:24,926 --> 02:45:29,353
Sounds of cheering came to us a few
moments later from the bunk house.

3068
02:45:29,353 --> 02:45:33,350
Evidently he had “begun right away,”
as the Judge had directed.

3069
02:45:33,350 --> 02:45:39,977
He had told his fortune to his brother
cowpunchers, and this was their answer.

3070
02:45:39,977 --> 02:45:42,143
“I wonder if Trampas is shouting too?”

3071
02:45:42,143 --> 02:45:43,257
inquired Ogden.

3072
02:45:43,257 --> 02:45:44,047
“Hm!”

3073
02:45:44,047 --> 02:45:45,138
said the Judge.

3074
02:45:45,138 --> -1:59:59,000
“That is one of the particulars I
wash my hands of.

3075
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3076
02:45:48,362 --> 02:45:51,018
I knew that he entirely meant it.

3077
02:45:51,018 --> 02:45:56,100
I knew, once his decision taken of
appointing the Virginian his lieutenant

3078
02:45:56,100 --> 02:45:59,317
for good and all, that,
like a wise commander-in-chief,

3079
02:45:59,317 --> 02:46:03,245
he would trust his lieutenant to take
care of his own business.

3080
02:46:03,245 --> 02:46:08,644
“Well,” Ogden pursued with interest,
“haven’t you landed Trampas

3081
02:46:08,644 --> 02:46:10,091
plump at his mercy?”

3082
02:46:10,091 --> 02:46:12,537
The phrase tickled the Judge.

3083
02:46:12,537 --> 02:46:14,180
“That is where I’ve landed him!”

3084
02:46:14,180 --> 02:46:14,988
he declared.

3085
02:46:14,988 --> 02:46:17,074
“And here is Dr. MacBride.”

3086
02:46:17,074 --> 02:46:18,540
CHAPTER XXI

3087
02:46:18,540 --> 02:46:19,460
In a State of Sin

3088
02:46:19,460 --> 02:46:23,594
Thunder sat imminent upon
the missionary’s brow.

3089
02:46:23,594 --> 02:46:25,983
Many were to be at his mercy soon.

3090
02:46:25,983 --> 02:46:28,234
But for us he had sunshine still.

3091
02:46:28,234 --> 02:46:32,895
“I am truly sorry to be turning you
upside down,” he said importantly.

3092
02:46:32,895 --> 02:46:35,153
“But it seems the best
place for my service.”

3093
02:46:35,153 --> 02:46:38,496
He spoke of the tables pushed back and
the chairs gathered in the hall,

3094
02:46:38,496 --> 02:46:41,135
where the storm would presently
break upon the congregation.

3095
02:46:41,135 --> 02:46:41,895
“Eight-thirty?”

3096
02:46:41,895 --> 02:46:43,356
he inquired.

3097
02:46:43,356 --> 02:46:47,552
This was the hour appointed,
and it was only twenty minutes off.

3098
02:46:47,552 --> 02:46:52,135
We threw the unsmoked fractions of our
cigars away, and returned to offer our

3099
02:46:52,135 --> 02:46:54,135
services to the ladies.

3100
02:46:54,135 --> 02:46:56,035
This amused the ladies.

3101
02:46:56,035 --> 02:46:57,374
They had done without us.

3102
02:46:57,374 --> 02:47:00,451
All was ready in the hall.

3103
02:47:00,451 --> 02:47:04,319
“We got the cook to help us,”
Mrs. Ogden told me, “so as not

3104
02:47:04,319 --> 02:47:06,301
to disturb your cigars.

3105
02:47:06,301 --> 02:47:10,467
In spite of the cowboys,
I still recognize my own country.”

3106
02:47:10,467 --> 02:47:11,354
“In the cook?”

3107
02:47:11,354 --> 02:47:13,344
I rather densely asked.

3108
02:47:13,344 --> 02:47:15,624
“Oh, no!

3109
02:47:15,624 --> 02:47:17,566
I don’t have a Chinaman.

3110
02:47:17,566 --> -1:59:59,000
It’s in the length of after-dinner cigars.

3111
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3112
02:47:21,549 --> 02:47:24,370
“Had you been smoking,”
I returned, “you would have found

3113
02:47:24,370 --> 02:47:25,610
them short this evening.”

3114
02:47:25,610 --> 02:47:30,016
“You make it worse,” said the lady;
“we have had nothing but Dr. MacBride.”

3115
02:47:30,016 --> 02:47:33,582
“We’ll share him with
you now,” I exclaimed.

3116
02:47:33,582 --> 02:47:36,251
“Has he announced his text?

3117
02:47:36,251 --> 02:47:40,163
I’ve got one for him,”
said Molly Wood, joining us.

3118
02:47:40,163 --> 02:47:43,464
She stood on tiptoe and spoke it
comically in our ears.

3119
02:47:43,464 --> -1:59:59,000
“ ‘I said in my haste, All men are liars.’

3120
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3121
02:47:46,426 --> 02:47:50,946
This made us merry as we stood among the
chairs in the congested hall.

3122
02:47:50,946 --> 02:47:54,048
I left the ladies, and
sought the bunk house.

3123
02:47:54,048 --> 02:47:57,689
I had heard the cheers,
but I was curious also to see the men,

3124
02:47:57,689 --> 02:47:59,169
and how they were taking it.

3125
02:47:59,169 --> 02:48:02,215
There was but little for the eye.

3126
02:48:02,215 --> 02:48:04,262
There was much noise in the room.

3127
02:48:04,262 --> 02:48:07,609
They were getting ready to come to
church⁠—brushing their hair,

3128
02:48:07,609 --> 02:48:11,772
shaving, and making themselves clean,
amid talk occasionally

3129
02:48:11,772 --> 02:48:14,613
profane and continuously diverting.

3130
02:48:14,613 --> 02:48:18,155
“Well, I’m a Christian,
anyway,” one declared.

3131
02:48:18,155 --> 02:48:20,656
“I’m a Mormon, I guess,” said another.

3132
02:48:20,656 --> 02:48:25,168
“I belong to the Knights of
Pythias,” said a third.

3133
02:48:25,168 --> 02:48:28,612
“I’m a Mohammedist,” said a fourth;
“I hope I ain’t goin’ to hear

3134
02:48:28,612 --> -1:59:59,000
nothin’ to shock me.

3135
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3136
02:48:29,640 --> 02:48:31,233
And they went on with their joking.

3137
02:48:31,233 --> 02:48:33,912
But Trampas was out of the joking.

3138
02:48:33,912 --> 02:48:37,932
He lay on his bed reading a newspaper,
and took no pains to look pleasant.

3139
02:48:37,932 --> 02:48:42,060
My eyes were considering him when the
blithe Scipio came in.

3140
02:48:42,060 --> 02:48:44,318
“Don’t look so bashful,” said he.

3141
02:48:44,318 --> 02:48:45,816
“There’s only us girls here.”

3142
02:48:45,816 --> 02:48:49,373
He had been helping the Virginian move
his belongings from the bunk house over

3143
02:48:49,373 --> 02:48:50,631
to the foreman’s cabin.

3144
02:48:50,631 --> 02:48:55,075
He himself was to occupy the
Virginian’s old bed here.

3145
02:48:55,075 --> 02:48:59,245
“And I hope sleepin’ in it will bring me
some of his luck,” said Scipio.

3146
02:48:59,245 --> 02:49:03,828
“Yu’d ought to’ve seen us when he told us
in his quiet way.

3147
02:49:03,828 --> 02:49:07,977
Well,” Scipio sighed a little,
“it must feel good to have your

3148
02:49:07,977 --> 02:49:09,478
friends glad about you.”

3149
02:49:09,478 --> 02:49:13,065
“Especially Trampas,” said I.

3150
02:49:13,065 --> 02:49:15,798
“The Judge knows about that,” I added.

3151
02:49:15,798 --> 02:49:17,538
“Knows, does he?

3152
02:49:17,538 --> 02:49:18,557
What’s he say?”

3153
02:49:18,557 --> 02:49:21,277
Scipio drew me quickly out
of the bunk house.

3154
02:49:21,277 --> 02:49:23,239
“Says it’s no business of his.”

3155
02:49:23,239 --> 02:49:24,480
“Said nothing but that?”

3156
02:49:24,480 --> 02:49:29,122
Scipio’s curiosity seemed
strangely intense.

3157
02:49:29,122 --> 02:49:31,381
“Made no suggestion?

3158
02:49:31,381 --> 02:49:32,522
Not a thing?”

3159
02:49:32,522 --> 02:49:33,477
“Not a thing.

3160
02:49:33,477 --> 02:49:36,423
Said he didn’t want to
know and didn’t care.”

3161
02:49:36,423 --> 02:49:39,026
“How did he happen to hear about it?”

3162
02:49:39,026 --> 02:49:40,066
snapped Scipio.

3163
02:49:40,066 --> 02:49:41,160
“You told him!”

3164
02:49:41,160 --> 02:49:42,746
he immediately guessed.

3165
02:49:42,746 --> 02:49:43,946
“He never would.”

3166
02:49:43,946 --> 02:49:47,786
And Scipio jerked his thumb at the
Virginian, who appeared for a moment in

3167
02:49:47,786 --> 02:49:50,679
the lighted window of the new
quarters he was arranging.

3168
02:49:50,679 --> 02:49:53,561
“He never would tell,” Scipio repeated.

3169
02:49:53,561 --> 02:49:58,166
“And so the Judge never made a suggestion
to him,” he muttered,

3170
02:49:58,166 --> 02:50:00,210
nodding in the darkness.

3171
02:50:00,210 --> 02:50:03,300
“So it’s just his own notion.

3172
02:50:03,300 --> 02:50:07,093
Just like him, too, come to think of it.

3173
02:50:07,093 --> 02:50:10,715
Only I didn’t expect⁠—well,
I guess he could surprise me

3174
02:50:10,715 --> -1:59:59,000
any day he tried.

3175
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3176
02:50:12,247 --> 02:50:14,939
“You’re surprising me now,” I said.

3177
02:50:14,939 --> 02:50:16,107
“What’s it all about?”

3178
02:50:16,107 --> 02:50:18,820
“Oh, him and Trampas.”

3179
02:50:18,820 --> 02:50:19,407
“What?

3180
02:50:19,407 --> 02:50:20,758
Nothing surely happened yet?”

3181
02:50:20,758 --> 02:50:22,962
I was as curious as Scipio had been.

3182
02:50:22,962 --> 02:50:24,862
“No, not yet.

3183
02:50:24,862 --> 02:50:26,216
But there will.”

3184
02:50:26,216 --> 02:50:27,542
“Great Heavens, man!

3185
02:50:27,542 --> 02:50:28,124
when?”

3186
02:50:28,124 --> 02:50:33,122
“Just as soon as Trampas makes the first
move,” Scipio replied easily.

3187
02:50:33,122 --> 02:50:34,747
I became dignified.

3188
02:50:34,747 --> 02:50:39,227
Scipio had evidently been told
things by the Virginian.

3189
02:50:39,227 --> 02:50:44,083
“Yes, I up and asked him
plumb out,” Scipio answered.

3190
02:50:44,083 --> 02:50:48,587
“I was liftin’ his trunk in at the door,
and I couldn’t stand it no longer,

3191
02:50:48,587 --> 02:50:50,243
and I asked him plumb out.

3192
02:50:50,243 --> 02:50:53,053
‘Yu’ve sure got Trampas
where yu’ want him.’

3193
02:50:53,053 --> 02:50:54,844
That’s what I said.

3194
02:50:54,844 --> 02:50:57,414
And he up and answered and told me.

3195
02:50:57,414 --> 02:50:58,470
So I know.”

3196
02:50:58,470 --> 02:51:01,881
At this point Scipio stopped;
I was not to know.

3197
02:51:01,881 --> 02:51:04,994
“I had no idea,” I said,
“that your system held so much

3198
02:51:04,994 --> 02:51:06,016
meanness.”

3199
02:51:06,016 --> 02:51:09,068
“Oh, it ain’t meanness!”

3200
02:51:09,068 --> 02:51:11,090
And he laughed ecstatically.

3201
02:51:11,090 --> 02:51:12,643
“What do you call it, then?”

3202
02:51:12,643 --> 02:51:16,844
“He’d call it discretion,” said Scipio.

3203
02:51:16,844 --> 02:51:18,684
Then he became serious.

3204
02:51:18,684 --> 02:51:20,825
“It’s too blamed grand to tell yu’.

3205
02:51:20,825 --> 02:51:23,286
I’ll leave yu’ to see it happen.

3206
02:51:23,286 --> 02:51:26,486
Keep around, that’s all.

3207
02:51:26,486 --> 02:51:27,445
Keep around.

3208
02:51:27,445 --> 02:51:29,608
I pretty near wish I didn’t
know it myself.”

3209
02:51:29,608 --> 02:51:34,477
What with my feelings at Scipio’s
discretion, and my human curiosity,

3210
02:51:34,477 --> 02:51:37,506
I was not in that mood which best
profits from a sermon.

3211
02:51:37,506 --> 02:51:42,460
Yet even though my expectations had been
cruelly left quivering in mid air,

3212
02:51:42,460 --> 02:51:46,959
I was not sure how much I really
wanted to “keep around.”

3213
02:51:46,959 --> 02:51:52,079
You will therefore understand how Dr.
MacBride was able to make a prayer and

3214
02:51:52,079 --> 02:51:57,835
to read Scripture without my being
conscious of a word that he had uttered.

3215
02:51:57,835 --> 02:52:02,182
It was when I saw him opening the
manuscript of his sermon that I suddenly

3216
02:52:02,182 --> 02:52:05,877
remembered I was sitting,
so to speak, in church,

3217
02:52:05,877 --> 02:52:09,923
and began once more to think of the
preacher and his congregation.

3218
02:52:09,923 --> 02:52:15,051
Our chairs were in the front line,
of course; but, being next the wall,

3219
02:52:15,051 --> 02:52:17,860
I could easily see the cowboys behind
me.

3220
02:52:17,860 --> 02:52:19,731
They were perfectly decorous.

3221
02:52:19,731 --> 02:52:24,123
If Mrs. Ogden had looked for pistols,
daredevil attitudes,

3222
02:52:24,123 --> 02:52:27,124
and so forth, she must
have been greatly disappointed.

3223
02:52:27,124 --> 02:52:30,784
Except for their weather-beaten cheeks
and eyes, they were simply American

3224
02:52:30,784 --> 02:52:34,286
young men with mustaches and without,
and might have been sitting,

3225
02:52:34,286 --> 02:52:36,766
say, in Danbury, Connecticut.

3226
02:52:36,766 --> 02:52:41,807
Even Trampas merged quietly
with the general placidity.

3227
02:52:41,807 --> 02:52:45,651
The Virginian did not,
to be sure, look like Danbury,

3228
02:52:45,651 --> 02:52:50,322
and his frame and his features showed
out of the mass; but his eyes were upon

3229
02:52:50,322 --> 02:52:53,814
Dr. MacBride with a creamlike propriety.

3230
02:52:53,814 --> 02:52:57,574
Our missionary did not
choose Miss Wood’s text.

3231
02:52:57,574 --> 02:53:02,107
He made his selection from another of the
Psalms; and when it came,

3232
02:53:02,107 --> 02:53:05,987
I did not dare to look at anybody;
I was much nearer unseemly

3233
02:53:05,987 --> 02:53:08,074
conduct than the cowboys.

3234
02:53:08,074 --> 02:53:08,227
Dr.

3235
02:53:08,227 --> 02:53:13,208
MacBride gave us his text sonorously,
“ ‘They are altogether become filthy;

3236
02:53:13,208 --> -1:59:59,000
There is none of them that doeth
good, no, not one.’

3237
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3238
02:53:16,587 --> 02:53:21,326
His eye showed us plainly that present
company was not excepted from this.

3239
02:53:21,326 --> 02:53:25,563
He repeated the text once more,
then, launching upon his discourse,

3240
02:53:25,563 --> 02:53:28,469
gave none of us a ray of hope.

3241
02:53:28,469 --> 02:53:34,131
I had heard it all often before;
but preached to cowboys it took on a new

3242
02:53:34,131 --> 02:53:39,494
glare of untimeliness,
of grotesque obsoleteness⁠—as if someone

3243
02:53:39,494 --> 02:53:44,707
should say, “Let me persuade you to
admire woman,” and forthwith hold out

3244
02:53:44,707 --> 02:53:46,516
her bleached bones to you.

3245
02:53:46,516 --> 02:53:51,369
The cowboys were told that not only they
could do no good, but that if they did

3246
02:53:51,369 --> 02:53:53,609
contrive to, it would not help them.

3247
02:53:53,609 --> 02:54:01,136
Nay, more: not only honest deeds availed
them nothing, but even if they accepted

3248
02:54:01,136 --> 02:54:06,949
this especial creed which was being
explained to them as necessary for

3249
02:54:06,949 --> 02:54:10,455
salvation, still it might not save them.

3250
02:54:10,455 --> 02:54:15,689
Their sin was indeed the cause of their
damnation, yet, keeping from sin,

3251
02:54:15,689 --> 02:54:17,985
they might nevertheless be lost.

3252
02:54:17,985 --> 02:54:21,240
It had all been settled for them not only
before they were born,

3253
02:54:21,240 --> 02:54:22,718
but before Adam was shaped.

3254
02:54:22,718 --> 02:54:26,957
Having told them this,
he invited them to glorify the

3255
02:54:26,957 --> 02:54:29,544
Creator of the scheme.

3256
02:54:29,544 --> 02:54:32,709
Even if damned, they must praise the
person who had made them

3257
02:54:32,709 --> 02:54:34,549
expressly for damnation.

3258
02:54:34,549 --> 02:54:38,495
That is what I heard him prove by
logic to these cowboys.

3259
02:54:38,495 --> 02:54:42,905
Stone upon stone he built the black
cellar of his theology,

3260
02:54:42,905 --> 02:54:47,422
leaving out its beautiful park and the
sunshine of its garden.

3261
02:54:47,422 --> 02:54:51,964
He did not tell them the splendor of its
past, the noble fortress for good that

3262
02:54:51,964 --> 02:54:55,365
it had been, how its tonic had
strengthened generations

3263
02:54:55,365 --> 02:54:56,150
of their fathers.

3264
02:54:56,150 --> 02:55:00,106
No; wrath he spoke of,
and never once of love.

3265
02:55:00,106 --> 02:55:04,746
It was the bishop’s way,
I knew well, to hold cowboys by homely

3266
02:55:04,746 --> 02:55:08,060
talk of their special
hardships and temptations.

3267
02:55:08,060 --> 02:55:12,269
And when they fell he spoke to them of
forgiveness and brought

3268
02:55:12,269 --> 02:55:13,591
them encouragement.

3269
02:55:13,591 --> 02:55:18,743
But Dr. MacBride never thought once of
the lives of these waifs.

3270
02:55:18,743 --> 02:55:23,792
Like himself, like all mankind,
they were invisible dots in creation;

3271
02:55:23,792 --> 02:55:26,712
like him, they were to feel as nothing,
to be swept up in the potent

3272
02:55:26,712 --> 02:55:26,752
heat of his faith.

3273
02:55:26,752 --> 02:55:30,497
So he thrust out to them none of the
sweet but all the bitter of his creed,

3274
02:55:30,497 --> 02:55:33,159
naked and stern as iron.

3275
02:55:33,159 --> 02:55:37,118
Dogma was his all in all,
and poor humanity was nothing but

3276
02:55:37,118 --> 02:55:39,022
flesh for its canons.

3277
02:55:39,022 --> 02:55:44,450
Thus to kill what chance he had for being
of use seemed to me more deplorable than

3278
02:55:44,450 --> 02:55:46,075
it did evidently to them.

3279
02:55:46,075 --> 02:55:48,416
Their attention merely wandered.

3280
02:55:48,416 --> 02:55:51,690
Three hundred years ago they would have
been frightened; but not

3281
02:55:51,690 --> 02:55:53,051
in this electric day.

3282
02:55:53,051 --> 02:55:59,421
I saw Scipio stifling a smile when it
came to the doctrine of original sin.

3283
02:55:59,421 --> 02:56:03,735
“We know of its truth,”
said Dr. MacBride, “from the severe

3284
02:56:03,735 --> 02:56:09,767
troubles and distresses to which infants
are liable, and from death passing upon

3285
02:56:09,767 --> -1:59:59,000
them before they are capable of sinning.

3286
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3287
02:56:12,202 --> 02:56:16,767
Yet I knew he was a good man;
and I also knew that if a missionary is

3288
02:56:16,767 --> 02:56:20,466
to be tactless, he might almost
as well be bad.

3289
02:56:20,466 --> 02:56:23,887
I said their attention wandered,
but I forgot the Virginian.

3290
02:56:23,887 --> 02:56:29,129
At first his attitude might
have been mere propriety.

3291
02:56:29,129 --> 02:56:34,065
One can look respectfully at a preacher
and be internally breaking

3292
02:56:34,065 --> 02:56:35,612
all the commandments.

3293
02:56:35,612 --> 02:56:39,792
But even with the text I saw real
attention light in the Virginian’s eye.

3294
02:56:39,792 --> 02:56:44,667
And keeping track of the concentration
that grew on him with each minute made

3295
02:56:44,667 --> 02:56:46,237
the sermon short for me.

3296
02:56:46,237 --> 02:56:47,942
He missed nothing.

3297
02:56:47,942 --> 02:56:52,558
Before the end his gaze at the
preacher had become swerveless.

3298
02:56:52,558 --> 02:56:56,252
Was he convert or critic?

3299
02:56:56,252 --> 02:56:58,252
Convert was incredible.

3300
02:56:58,252 --> 02:57:05,352
Thus was an hour passed before I
had thought of time.

3301
02:57:05,352 --> 02:57:09,693
When it was over we took it variously.

3302
02:57:09,693 --> 02:57:14,227
The preacher was genial and spoke of
having now broken ground for the lessons

3303
02:57:14,227 --> 02:57:15,649
that he hoped to instill.

3304
02:57:15,649 --> 02:57:19,867
He discoursed for a while about trout-
fishing and about the rumored uneasiness

3305
02:57:19,867 --> 02:57:22,200
of the Indians northward
where he was going.

3306
02:57:22,200 --> 02:57:25,998
It was plain that his personal safety
never gave him a thought.

3307
02:57:25,998 --> 02:57:28,428
He soon bade us good night.

3308
02:57:28,428 --> 02:57:31,938
The Ogdens shrugged their
shoulders and were amused.

3309
02:57:31,938 --> 02:57:33,751
That was their way of taking it.

3310
02:57:33,751 --> 02:57:34,316
Dr.

3311
02:57:34,316 --> 02:57:38,131
MacBride sat too heavily on the Judge’s
shoulders for him to shrug them.

3312
02:57:38,131 --> 02:57:43,653
As a leading citizen in the Territory he
kept open house for all comers.

3313
02:57:43,653 --> 02:57:49,553
Policy and good nature made him bid
welcome a wide variety of travellers.

3314
02:57:49,553 --> 02:57:54,342
The cowboy out of employment found bed
and a meal for himself and his horse,

3315
02:57:54,342 --> 02:57:59,241
and missionaries had before now been
well received at Sunk Creek Ranch.

3316
02:57:59,241 --> 02:58:03,151
“I suppose I’ll have to take him
fishing,” said the Judge, ruefully.

3317
02:58:03,151 --> 02:58:06,002
“Yes, my dear,” said his wife, “you will.

3318
02:58:06,002 --> 02:58:08,772
And I shall have to make his
tea for six days.”

3319
02:58:08,772 --> 02:58:11,962
“Otherwise,” Ogden suggested,
“it might be reported that you

3320
02:58:11,962 --> 02:58:13,442
were enemies of religion.”

3321
02:58:13,442 --> 02:58:15,042
“That’s about it,” said the Judge.

3322
02:58:15,042 --> 02:58:17,621
“I can get on with most people.

3323
02:58:17,621 --> 02:58:20,057
But elephants depress me.”

3324
02:58:20,057 --> 02:58:24,795
So we named the Doctor “Jumbo,”
and I departed to my quarters.

3325
02:58:24,795 --> 02:58:30,634
At the bunk house, the comments were
similar but more highly salted.

3326
02:58:30,634 --> 02:58:32,320
The men were going to bed.

3327
02:58:32,320 --> 02:58:36,763
In spite of their outward decorum at the
service, they had not liked to be told

3328
02:58:36,763 --> 02:58:43,874
that they were “altogether
become filthy.”

3329
02:58:44,006 --> 02:58:52,212
It was easy to call names;
they could do that themselves.

3330
02:58:52,212 --> 02:59:02,497
And they appealed to me,
several speaking at once,

3331
02:59:02,497 --> 02:59:09,742
like a concerted piece at the opera:
“Say, do you believe babies go to hell?”

3332
02:59:09,742 --> 02:59:15,262
⁠—“Ah, of course he don’t.”
⁠—“There ain’t no hereafter,

3333
02:59:15,262 --> 02:59:24,102
anyway.”⁠—“Ain’t there?”⁠—“Who told
yu’?”⁠—“Same man as told the preacher we

3334
02:59:24,102 --> 02:59:31,269
were all a sifted set of sons-of-guns.

3335
02:59:31,269 --> 02:59:35,133
”⁠—“Well, I’m going to stay a Mormon.

3336
02:59:35,133 --> 02:59:43,227
”⁠—“Well, I’m going to quit
fleeing from temptation.”⁠—“that

3337
02:59:43,227 --> 02:59:44,667
’s so!

3338
02:59:44,667 --> 02:59:50,488
Better get it in the neck after a good
time than a poor one.”

3339
02:59:50,488 --> 02:59:53,085
And so forth.

3340
02:59:53,085 --> 02:59:59,979
Their wit was not extreme,
yet I should like Dr. MacBride

3341
02:59:59,979 --> 03:00:02,372
to have heard it.

3342
03:00:02,372 --> 03:00:11,453
One fellow put his natural soul pretty
well into words, “If I happened to learn

3343
03:00:11,453 --> 03:00:16,757
what they had predestinated me to do,
I’d do the other thing,

3344
03:00:16,757 --> 03:00:19,599
just to show ’em!”

3345
03:00:19,599 --> 03:00:21,749
And Trampas?

3346
03:00:21,749 --> 03:00:23,710
And the Virginian?

3347
03:00:23,710 --> 03:00:25,669
They were out of it.

3348
03:00:25,669 --> 03:00:30,340
The Virginian had gone straight
to his new abode.

3349
03:00:30,340 --> 03:00:38,902
Trampas lay in his bed,
not asleep, and sullen as ever.

3350
03:00:38,902 --> 03:00:44,342
“He ain’t got religion this trip,”
said Scipio to me.

3351
03:00:44,342 --> 03:00:47,622
“Did his new foreman get it?”

3352
03:00:47,622 --> 03:00:49,222
I asked.

3353
03:00:49,222 --> 03:00:50,382
“Huh!

3354
03:00:50,382 --> 03:00:53,083
It would spoil him.

3355
03:00:53,083 --> 03:00:55,603
You keep around that’s all.

3356
03:00:55,603 --> 03:00:56,923
Keep around.”

3357
03:00:56,923 --> 03:01:04,286
Scipio was not to be probed;
and I went, still baffled, to my repose.

3358
03:01:04,286 --> 03:01:11,047
No light burned in the cabin as
I approached its door.

3359
03:01:11,047 --> 03:01:22,106
The Virginian’s room was quiet and dark;
and that Dr. MacBride slumbered was

3360
03:01:22,106 --> 03:01:31,299
plainly audible to me,
even before I entered.

3361
03:01:31,299 --> -1:59:59,000
Go fishing with him

3362
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
!

3363
03:01:35,459 --> 03:01:39,672
I thought, as I undressed.

3364
03:01:39,672 --> 03:01:45,376
And I selfishly decided that the Judge
might have this privilege

3365
03:01:45,376 --> 03:01:48,639
entirely to himself.

3366
03:01:48,639 --> 03:01:54,619
Sleep came to me fairly soon,
in spite of the Doctor.

3367
03:01:54,619 --> 03:02:05,113
I was wakened from it by my bed’s being
jolted⁠—not a pleasant thing that night.

3368
03:02:05,113 --> 03:02:08,095
I must have started.

3369
03:02:08,095 --> 03:02:14,418
And it was the quiet voice of the
Virginian that told me he was sorry to

3370
03:02:14,418 --> 03:02:19,872
have accidentally disturbed me.

3371
03:02:19,872 --> 03:02:24,152
This disturbed me a good deal more.

3372
03:02:24,152 --> 03:02:30,376
But his steps did not go to the bunk
house, as my sensational

3373
03:02:30,376 --> 03:02:34,248
mind had suggested.

3374
03:02:34,248 --> 03:02:37,559
He was not wearing much,
and in the dimness he

3375
03:02:37,559 --> 03:02:41,552
seemed taller than common.

3376
03:02:41,552 --> 03:02:53,750
I next made out that he was
bending over Dr. MacBride.

3377
03:02:53,750 --> 03:02:57,721
The divine at last sprang upright.

3378
03:02:57,721 --> 03:03:00,761
“I am armed,” he said.

3379
03:03:00,761 --> 03:03:03,548
“Take care.

3380
03:03:03,548 --> 03:03:05,578
Who are you?”

3381
03:03:05,578 --> 03:03:09,978
“You can lay down your gun, seh.

3382
03:03:09,978 --> 03:03:15,778
I feel like my spirit was
going to bear witness.

3383
03:03:15,778 --> 03:03:21,258
I feel like I might get an enlightening.”

3384
03:03:21,310 --> 03:03:28,190
He was using some of the
missionary’s own language.

3385
03:03:28,190 --> 03:03:38,135
The baffling I had been treated to by
Scipio melted to nothing in this.

3386
03:03:38,135 --> 03:03:47,526
Did living men petrify,
I should have changed to

3387
03:03:47,526 --> 03:03:50,446
mineral between the sheets.

3388
03:03:50,446 --> 03:03:59,078
The Doctor got out of bed,
lighted his lamp, and found a book;

3389
03:03:59,078 --> 03:04:06,529
and the two retired into the Virginian’s
room, where I could hear the

3390
03:04:06,529 --> 03:04:11,259
exhortations as I lay amazed.

3391
03:04:11,259 --> 03:04:19,740
In time the Doctor returned,
blew out his lamp, and settled himself.

3392
03:04:19,740 --> 03:04:27,912
I had been very much awake,
but was nearly gone to sleep again,

3393
03:04:27,912 --> 03:04:35,052
when the door creaked and the Virginian
stood by the Doctor’s side.

3394
03:04:35,052 --> 03:04:37,345
“Are you awake, seh?”

3395
03:04:37,345 --> 03:04:38,457
“What?

3396
03:04:38,457 --> 03:04:41,718
What’s that?

3397
03:04:41,718 --> 03:04:44,880
What is it?”

3398
03:04:44,880 --> 03:04:47,360
“Excuse me, seh.

3399
03:04:47,360 --> 03:04:49,372
The enemy is winning on me.

3400
03:04:49,372 --> 03:04:53,892
I’m feeling less inward
opposition to sin.”

3401
03:04:53,892 --> 03:04:58,230
The lamp was lighted,
and I listened to some

3402
03:04:58,230 --> 03:05:03,786
further exhortations.

3403
03:05:04,617 --> 03:05:08,857
They must have taken half an hour.

3404
03:05:08,857 --> 03:05:17,419
When the Doctor was in bed again,
I thought that I heard him sigh.

3405
03:05:17,419 --> 03:05:33,186
This upset my composure in the dark;
but I lay face downward in the pillow,

3406
03:05:33,186 --> 03:05:38,029
and the Doctor was soon again snoring.

3407
03:05:38,029 --> 03:05:44,949
I envied him for a while his
faculty of easy sleep.

3408
03:05:44,949 --> 03:05:56,464
But I must have dropped off myself;
for it was the lamp in my eyes that now

3409
03:05:56,464 --> 03:06:03,475
waked me as he came back for the third
time from the Virginian’s room.

3410
03:06:03,475 --> 03:06:12,795
Before blowing the light out he looked at
his watch, and thereupon I inquired

3411
03:06:12,795 --> 03:06:15,195
the hour of him.

3412
03:06:15,195 --> 03:06:17,515
“Three,” said he.

3413
03:06:17,515 --> 03:06:22,675
I could not sleep any more now,
and I lay watching the darkness.

3414
03:06:22,675 --> 03:06:26,115
“I’m afeared to be alone!”

3415
03:06:26,115 --> 03:06:33,371
said the Virginian’s voice presently
in the next room.

3416
03:06:33,371 --> 03:06:34,921
“I’m afeared.”

3417
03:06:34,921 --> 03:06:43,863
There was a short pause,
and then he shouted very loud,

3418
03:06:43,863 --> 03:06:51,468
“I’m losin’ my desire afteh the sincere
milk of the Word!”

3419
03:06:51,468 --> 03:06:52,975
“What?

3420
03:06:52,975 --> 03:06:54,574
What’s that?

3421
03:06:54,574 --> 03:06:56,877
What?”

3422
03:06:56,877 --> 03:07:07,538
The Doctor’s cot gave a great crack as he
started up listening,

3423
03:07:07,538 --> 03:07:11,138
and I put my face deep in the pillow.

3424
03:07:11,138 --> 03:07:13,098
“I’m afeared!

3425
03:07:13,098 --> 03:07:15,458
I’m afeared!

3426
03:07:15,458 --> 03:07:22,298
Sin has quit being bitter in my belly.”

3427
03:07:22,618 --> 03:07:26,258
“Courage, my good man.”

3428
03:07:26,258 --> 03:07:35,258
The Doctor was out of bed with his lamp
again, and the door shut behind him.

3429
03:07:35,258 --> 03:07:40,411
Between them they made it long this time.

3430
03:07:40,411 --> 03:07:47,313
I saw the window become gray;
then the corners of the furniture grow

3431
03:07:47,313 --> 03:07:52,473
visible; and outside,
the dry chorus of the blackbirds began

3432
03:07:52,473 --> 03:07:54,513
to fill the dawn.

3433
03:07:54,513 --> 03:08:02,047
To these the sounds of chickens and
impatient hoofs in the stable were

3434
03:08:02,047 --> 03:08:08,588
added, and some cow wandered by loudly
calling for her calf.

3435
03:08:08,588 --> 03:08:16,953
Next, someone whistling passed
near and grew distant.

3436
03:08:16,953 --> 03:08:22,514
But although the cold hue that I lay
staring at through the window warmed and

3437
03:08:22,514 --> 03:08:31,034
changed, the Doctor continued working
hard over his patient in the next room.

3438
03:08:31,034 --> 03:08:39,597
Only a word here and there was distinct;
but it was plain from the Virginian’s

3439
03:08:39,597 --> 03:08:46,409
fewer remarks that the sin in his belly
was alarming him less.

3440
03:08:46,409 --> 03:08:49,679
Yes, they made this time long.

3441
03:08:49,679 --> 03:08:55,371
But it proved, indeed, the last one.

3442
03:08:55,371 --> 03:09:01,146
And though some sort of catastrophe was
bound to fall upon us,

3443
03:09:01,146 --> 03:09:08,306
it was myself who precipitated the
thing that did happen.

3444
03:09:08,306 --> 03:09:11,898
Day was wholly come.

3445
03:09:11,898 --> 03:09:17,871
I looked at my own watch, and it was six.

3446
03:09:17,871 --> 03:09:26,002
I had been about seven hours in my bed,
and the Doctor had been about seven

3447
03:09:26,002 --> 03:09:28,002
hours out of his.

3448
03:09:28,002 --> 03:09:35,720
The door opened, and he came in with
his book and lamp.

3449
03:09:35,720 --> 03:09:40,680
He seemed to be shivering a little,
and I saw him cast a longing

3450
03:09:40,680 --> 03:09:42,641
eye at his couch.

3451
03:09:42,641 --> 03:09:50,521
But the Virginian followed him even as he
blew out the now quite superfluous

3452
03:09:50,521 --> 03:09:51,572
light.

3453
03:09:51,572 --> 03:09:58,646
They made a noticeable couple in their
underclothes: the Virginian with his

3454
03:09:58,646 --> 03:10:03,665
lean racehorse shanks running to a point
at his ankle, and the Doctor with his

3455
03:10:03,665 --> 03:10:08,952
stomach and his fat sedentary calves.

3456
03:10:08,952 --> 03:10:15,961
“You’ll be going to breakfast and the
ladies, seh, pretty soon,”

3457
03:10:15,961 --> 03:10:24,550
said the Virginian, with
a chastened voice.

3458
03:10:24,550 --> 03:10:34,784
“But I’ll worry through the
day somehow without yu’.

3459
03:10:34,784 --> 03:10:39,945
And tonight you can turn your wolf
loose on me again.”

3460
03:10:39,945 --> 03:10:43,319
Once more it was no use.

3461
03:10:43,319 --> 03:10:51,446
My face was deep in the pillow,
but I made sounds as of a hen who

3462
03:10:51,446 --> 03:10:54,488
has laid an egg.

3463
03:10:54,488 --> 03:11:06,789
It broke on the Doctor with a total
instantaneous smash, quite like an egg.

3464
03:11:06,789 --> 03:11:10,829
He tried to speak calmly.

3465
03:11:10,829 --> 03:11:13,052
“This is a disgrace.

3466
03:11:13,052 --> 03:11:15,212
An infamous disgrace.

3467
03:11:15,212 --> 03:11:26,222
Never in my life have I⁠—” Words forsook
him, and his face grew redder.

3468
03:11:26,222 --> 03:11:28,618
“Never in my life⁠—”

3469
03:11:28,618 --> 03:11:37,893
He stopped again, because,
at the sight of him being dignified in

3470
03:11:37,893 --> 03:11:48,065
his red drawers, I was making the noise
of a dozen hens.

3471
03:11:48,065 --> 03:11:53,247
It was suddenly too much
for the Virginian.

3472
03:11:53,247 --> 03:11:57,687
He hastened into his room,
and there sank on the floor with his

3473
03:11:57,687 --> 03:11:59,927
head in his hands.

3474
03:11:59,927 --> 03:12:07,762
The Doctor immediately slammed the door
upon him, and this rendered me easily

3475
03:12:07,762 --> 03:12:10,847
fit for a lunatic asylum.

3476
03:12:10,847 --> 03:12:15,922
I cried into my pillow,
and wondered if the Doctor would

3477
03:12:15,922 --> 03:12:18,522
come and kill me.

3478
03:12:18,522 --> 03:12:27,525
But he took no notice of me whatever.

3479
03:12:27,525 --> 03:12:35,793
I could hear the Virginian’s convulsions
through the door, and also

3480
03:12:35,793 --> 03:12:39,113
the Doctor furiously making

3481
03:12:39,113 --> 03:12:43,444
his toilet within three feet of my head

3482
03:12:43,444 --> 03:12:49,276
; and I lay quite still with my face the
other way, for I was really afraid

3483
03:12:49,276 --> 03:12:53,270
to look at him.

3484
03:12:53,270 --> 03:13:06,094
When I heard him walk to the door in his
boots, I ventured to peep;

3485
03:13:06,094 --> 03:13:14,228
and there he was, going out with his
bag in his hand.

3486
03:13:14,228 --> 03:13:20,979
As I still continued to lie,
weak and sore, and with a mind that had

3487
03:13:20,979 --> 03:13:27,692
ceased all operation,
the Virginian’s door opened.

3488
03:13:27,692 --> 03:13:43,692
He was clean and dressed and decent,
but the devil still sported in his eye.

3489
03:13:43,692 --> 03:13:52,023
I have never seen a creature
more irresistibly handsome.

3490
03:13:52,023 --> 03:13:57,863
Then my mind worked again.

3491
03:13:57,863 --> 03:14:01,001
“You’ve gone and done it,” said I.

3492
03:14:01,001 --> 03:14:03,703
“He’s packed his valise.

3493
03:14:03,703 --> 03:14:06,063
He’ll not sleep here.”

3494
03:14:06,063 --> 03:14:13,263
The Virginian looked quickly
out of the door.

3495
03:14:14,863 --> 03:14:18,463
“Why, he’s leavin’ us!”

3496
03:14:18,463 --> 03:14:20,545
he exclaimed.

3497
03:14:20,545 --> 03:14:28,345
“Drivin’ away right now in
his little old buggy!”

3498
03:14:29,725 --> 03:14:39,779
He turned to me, and our eyes met
solemnly over this large fact.

3499
03:14:39,779 --> 03:14:46,810
I thought that I perceived the faintest
tincture of dismay in the features of

3500
03:14:46,810 --> 03:14:59,551
Judge Henry’s new, responsible,
trusty foreman.

3501
03:14:59,551 --> 03:15:06,397
This was the first act
of his administration.

3502
03:15:06,397 --> 03:15:13,454
Once again he looked out
at the departing missionary.

3503
03:15:13,454 --> -1:59:59,000
“Well,” he vindictively stated,
“I cert’nly ain’t goin’ to run afteh him

3504
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
.”

3505
03:15:21,125 --> 03:15:24,471
And he looked at me again.

3506
03:15:24,471 --> 03:15:27,581
“Do you suppose the Judge knows?”

3507
03:15:27,581 --> 03:15:30,066
I inquired.

3508
03:15:30,066 --> 03:15:32,946
He shook his head.

3509
03:15:32,946 --> 03:15:38,825
“The windo’ shades is all
down still oveh yondeh.”

3510
03:15:38,825 --> 03:15:42,944
He paused.

3511
03:15:43,312 --> 03:15:51,188
“I don’t care,” he stated,
quite as if he had been ten years old.

3512
03:15:51,188 --> 03:15:55,814
Then he grinned guiltily.

3513
03:15:55,814 --> 03:16:00,597
“I was mighty respectful
to him all night.”

3514
03:16:00,597 --> 03:16:05,271
“Oh, yes, respectful!

3515
03:16:05,271 --> 03:16:10,614
Especially when you invited him to
turn his wolf loose.”

3516
03:16:10,614 --> 03:16:15,739
The Virginian gave a joyous gulp.

3517
03:16:15,739 --> 03:16:22,025
He now came and sat down on the
edge of my bed.

3518
03:16:22,025 --> 03:16:29,883
“I spoke awful good English to him most
of the time,” said he.

3519
03:16:29,883 --> 03:16:37,356
“I can, yu’ know, when I cinch my
attention tight on to it.

3520
03:16:37,356 --> 03:16:44,569
Yes, I cert’nly spoke a
lot o’ good English.

3521
03:16:44,569 --> 03:16:50,356
I didn’t understand some of it myself!”

3522
03:16:50,356 --> 03:16:55,583
He was now growing frankly
pleased with his exploit.

3523
03:16:55,583 --> 03:17:00,751
He had builded so much
better than he knew.

3524
03:17:00,751 --> 03:17:14,279
He got up and looked out across the
crystal world of light.

3525
03:17:14,279 --> 03:17:21,830
“The Doctor is at one-
mile crossing,” he said.

3526
03:17:21,830 --> 03:17:30,317
“He’ll get breakfast at the N-lazy-Y.”

3527
03:17:30,317 --> 03:17:41,359
Then he returned and sat again on my bed,
and began to give me his real heart.

3528
03:17:41,359 --> 03:17:46,959
“I never set up for being
better than others.

3529
03:17:46,959 --> 03:17:53,235
Not even to myself.

3530
03:17:53,235 --> 03:18:01,805
My thoughts ain’t apt to
travel around making comparisons.

3531
03:18:01,805 --> 03:18:10,499
And I shouldn’t wonder if my memory took
as much notice of the meannesses I have

3532
03:18:10,499 --> 03:18:13,631
done as of⁠—as of the other actions.

3533
03:18:13,631 --> 03:18:21,527
But to have to sit like a dumb lamb and
let a stranger tell yu’ for an hour that

3534
03:18:21,527 --> 03:18:27,898
yu’re a hawg and a swine,
just after you have acted in a way which

3535
03:18:27,898 --> 03:18:36,573
them that know the facts would
call pretty near white⁠—”

3536
03:18:36,573 --> 03:18:41,117
“Trampas!”

3537
03:18:41,117 --> 03:18:47,914
I could not help exclaiming.

3538
03:18:49,914 --> 03:18:58,354
For there are moments of insight when a
guess amounts to knowledge.

3539
03:18:59,014 --> 03:19:02,983
“Has Scipio told⁠—”

3540
03:19:02,983 --> 03:19:04,823
“No.

3541
03:19:04,823 --> 03:19:06,143
Not a word.

3542
03:19:06,143 --> 03:19:09,566
He wouldn’t tell me.”

3543
03:19:09,566 --> 03:19:16,658
“Well, yu’ see, I arrived home hyeh this
evenin’ with several thoughts workin’

3544
03:19:16,658 --> 03:19:20,018
and stirrin’ inside me.

3545
03:19:20,018 --> 03:19:27,093
And not one o’ them thoughts was
what yu’d call Christian.

3546
03:19:27,093 --> 03:19:32,535
I ain’t the least little
bit ashamed of ’em.

3547
03:19:32,535 --> 03:19:36,775
I’m a human.

3548
03:19:36,999 --> 03:19:44,450
But after the Judge⁠—well, yu’ heard him.

3549
03:19:44,450 --> 03:19:54,183
And so when I went away from that talk
and saw how positions was changed⁠—”

3550
03:19:54,183 --> 03:19:59,740
A step outside stopped him short.

3551
03:19:59,740 --> 03:20:05,691
Nothing more could be read in his face,
for there was Trampas himself

3552
03:20:05,691 --> 03:20:09,111
in the open door.

3553
03:20:09,111 --> 03:20:17,367
“Good morning,” said Trampas,
not looking at us.

3554
03:20:17,367 --> 03:20:22,403
He spoke with the same
cool sullenness of yesterday.

3555
03:20:22,403 --> 03:20:25,563
We returned his greeting.

3556
03:20:25,563 --> 03:20:35,292
“I believe I’m late in congratulating you
on your promotion,” said he.

3557
03:20:35,292 --> 03:20:39,213
The Virginian consulted his watch.

3558
03:20:39,213 --> 03:20:47,879
“It’s only half afteh six,” he returned.

3559
03:20:47,879 --> 03:20:52,388
Trampas’s sullenness deepened.

3560
03:20:52,388 --> 03:21:00,668
“Any man is to be congratulated on
getting a rise, I expect.”

3561
03:21:00,668 --> 03:21:05,979
This time the Virginian let him have it.

3562
03:21:05,979 --> 03:21:07,472
“Cert’nly.

3563
03:21:07,472 --> 03:21:13,031
And I ain’t forgetting how much I
owe mine to you.”

3564
03:21:13,031 --> 03:21:24,007
Trampas would have liked
to let himself go.

3565
03:21:24,007 --> 03:21:31,385
“I’ve not come here for
any forgiveness,” he sneered.

3566
03:21:31,385 --> 03:21:39,880
“When did yu’ feel yu’ needed any?”

3567
03:21:39,972 --> 03:21:53,362
The Virginian was impregnable.

3568
03:21:53,362 --> 03:22:03,510
Trampas seemed to feel how little he
was gaining this way.

3569
03:22:03,510 --> 03:22:13,180
He came out straight now.

3570
03:22:13,180 --> 03:22:19,180
“Oh, I haven’t any Judge
behind me, I know.

3571
03:22:19,180 --> 03:22:34,032
I heard you’d be paying the boys this
morning, and I’ve come for my time.”

3572
03:22:34,666 --> 03:22:41,519
“You’re thinking of leaving us?”

3573
03:22:41,519 --> 03:22:44,599
asked the new foreman.

3574
03:22:44,599 --> 03:22:49,744
“What’s your dissatisfaction?”

3575
03:22:49,744 --> 03:22:54,352
“Oh, I’m not needing anybody back of me.

3576
03:22:54,352 --> 03:22:59,709
I’ll get along by myself.”

3577
03:22:59,709 --> 03:23:09,620
It was thus he revealed his expectation
of being dismissed by his enemy.

3578
03:23:09,620 --> 03:23:17,036
This would have knocked any meditated
generosity out of my heart.

3579
03:23:17,036 --> 03:23:22,019
But I was not the Virginian.

3580
03:23:22,019 --> 03:23:32,371
He shifted his legs, leaned back
a little, and laughed.

3581
03:23:32,371 --> 03:23:51,082
“Go back to your job,
Trampas, if that’s all your complaint.

3582
03:23:51,082 --> 03:23:56,023
You’re right about me being in luck.

3583
03:23:56,023 --> -1:59:59,000
But maybe there’s two of us in luck.

3584
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3585
03:24:00,683 --> 03:24:11,666
It was this that Scipio had preferred me
to see with my own eyes.

3586
03:24:11,666 --> 03:24:18,326
The fight was between man
and man no longer.

3587
03:24:18,326 --> 03:24:25,256
The case could not be one of forgiveness;
but the Virginian would not use his

3588
03:24:25,256 --> 03:24:32,534
official position to
crush his subordinate.

3589
03:24:32,534 --> 03:24:45,375
Trampas departed with something muttered
that I did not hear,

3590
03:24:45,375 --> 03:24:56,571
and the Virginian closed intimate
conversation by saying,

3591
03:24:56,571 --> 03:25:02,079
“You’ll be late for breakfast.”

